config_element.name: dot11AssociationSAQueryRetryTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout (in TUs) before trying a Query Request frame.

config_element.name: unifiTestTxPowerEnable
config_element.description_user: Test only: Bitfield to enable Control Plane Tx Power processing.

config_element.name: unifiUserSetTxpowerLevel
config_element.description_user: Test only: Maximum User Set Tx Power (quarter dBm). Enable it in unifiTestTxPowerEnable.

config_element.name: unifiNoCellMaxPower
config_element.description_user: Max power values for included channels (quarter dBm).

config_element.name: unifiNoCellIncludedChannels
config_element.description_user: Channels applicable. Defined in a uint64 represented by the octet string. First byte of the octet string maps to LSB. Bit 0 maps to channel 1. Mapping defined in ChannelisationRules.

config_element.name: unifiSarBackoff
config_element.description_user: Max power values per band per index(quarter dBm).

config_element.name: unifiPowerIsGrip
config_element.description_user: Is using Grip power cap instead of SAR cap.

config_element.name: unifiTPCMaxPowerRSSIThreshold
config_element.description_user: Below the (dBm) threshold, switch to the max power allowed by regulatory, if it has been previously reduced due to unifiTPCMinPowerRSSIThreshold. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiTPCMinPowerRSSIThreshold
config_element.description_user: Above the (dBm) threshold, limit the transmit power by unifiTPCMaxPower2G/unifiTPCMaxPower5G. A Zero value reverts the power to a default state. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiTPCMaxPower2G
config_element.description_user: Maximum power for 2.4GHz SISO interface when RSSI is above unifiTPCMinPowerRSSIThreshold (quarter dbm). Should be greater than dot11PowerCapabilityMinImplemented. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiTPCMaxPower2GMIMO
config_element.description_user: Maximum power for 2.4GHz MIMO interface when RSSI is above unifiTPCMinPowerRSSIThreshold (quarter dbm). Should be greater than dot11PowerCapabilityMinImplemented. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiTPCMaxPower5G
config_element.description_user: Maximum power for 5 GHz SISO interface when RSSI is above unifiTPCMinPowerRSSIThreshold (quarter dbm). Should be greater than dot11PowerCapabilityMinImplemented. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiTPCMaxPower5GMIMO
config_element.description_user: Maximum power for 5 GHz MIMO interface when RSSI is above unifiTPCMinPowerRSSIThreshold (quarter dbm). Should be greater than dot11PowerCapabilityMinImplemented. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiTPCUseAfterConnectRsp
config_element.description_user: Use TPC only after MlmeConnect_Rsp has been received from the Host i.e. not during initial connection exchanges (EAPOL/DHCP operation) as RSSI readings might be inaccurate. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiLteCoexMaxPowerRSSIThreshold
config_element.description_user: Below this (dBm) threshold, switch to max power allowed by regulatory, if it has been previously reduced due to unifiTPCMinPowerRSSIThreshold. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiLteCoexMinPowerRSSIThreshold
config_element.description_user: Above this(dBm) threshold, switch to minimum hardware supported - capped by unifiTPCMaxPower2G/unifiTPCMaxPower5G. Zero reverts the power to its default state. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiLteCoexPowerReduction
config_element.description_user: When LTE Coex Power Reduction provisions are met, impose a power cap of the regulatory domain less the amount specified by this MIB (quarter dB). This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiPrivateBbbTxFilterConfig
config_element.description_user: entry is written directly to the BBB_TX_FILTER_CONFIG register. Only the lower eight bits of this register are implemented . Bits 0-3 are the 'Tx Gain', bits 6-8 are the 'Tx Delay'. This register should only be changed by an expert.

config_element.name: unifiDeactivateInessentialDebug
config_element.description_user: Allow Deactivate Inessential debug in high TRx throughput condition - default value is false.

config_element.name: unifiThroughputLow
config_element.description_user: Lower threshold for number of bytes received in a second - default value based on 300Mbps

config_element.name: unifiThroughputHigh
config_element.description_user: Upper threshold for number of bytes received in a second - default value based on 400Mbps

config_element.name: deprecated_unifiWapiQosMask
config_element.description_user: Forces the WAPI encryption hardware use the QoS mask specified.

config_element.name: unifiCSROnlyMIBShield
config_element.description_user: Each element of the MIB has a set of read/write access constraints that may be applied when the element is accessed by the host. For most elements the constants are derived from their MAX-ACCESS clauses. unifiCSROnlyMIBShield controls the access mechanism. If this entry is set to 'warn', when the host makes an inappropriate access to a MIB variable (e.g., writing to a 'read-only' entry) then the firmware attempts to send a warning message to the host, but access is allowed to the MIB variable. If this entry is set to 'guard' then inappropriate accesses from the host are prevented. If this entry is set to 'alarm' then inappropriate accesses from the host are prevented and the firmware attempts to send warning messages to the host. If this entry is set to 'open' then no access constraints are applied and now warnings issued. Note that certain MIB entries have further protection schemes. In particular, the MIB prevents the host from reading some security keys (WEP keys, etc.).

config_element.name: unifiPsPollThreshold
config_element.description_user: PS Poll threshold. When Unifi chip is configured for normal power save mode and when access point does not respond to PS-Poll requests, then a fault will be generated on non-zero PS Poll threshold indicating mode has been switched from power save to fast power save. Ignored PS Poll count is given as the fault argument.

config_element.name: unifiPostEBRTWindow
config_element.description_user: Minimum time after the expected normal mode beacon reception time that UniFi will continue to listen for the beacon in an infrastructure BSS before timing out. Reducing this value can reduce UniFi power consumption when using low power modes, however a value which is too small may cause beacons to be missed, requiring the radio to remain on for longer periods to ensure reception of the subsequent beacon.

config_element.name: unifiPostEBRTWindowIdle
config_element.description_user: Minimum time after the expected idle mode beacon reception time that UniFi will continue to listen for the beacon in an infrastructure BSS before timing out. Reducing this value can reduce UniFi power consumption when using low power modes, however a value which is too small may cause beacons to be missed, requiring the radio to remain on for longer periods to ensure reception of the subsequent beacon.

config_element.name: unifiCSROnlyPowerCalDelay
config_element.description_user: Delay applied at each step of the power calibration routine used with an external PA.

config_element.name: unifiPreEBRTWindow
config_element.description_user: Latest time before the expected beacon reception time that UniFi will turn on its radio in order to receive the beacon. Reducing this value can reduce UniFi power consumption when using low power modes, however a value which is too small may cause beacons to be missed, requiring the radio to remain on for longer periods to ensure reception of the subsequent beacon.

config_element.name: unifiPreEBRTWindowIdle
config_element.description_user: Latest time before the expected idle mode beacon reception time that UniFi will turn on its radio in order to receive the beacon. Reducing this value can reduce UniFi power consumption when using low power modes, however a value which is too small may cause beacons to be missed, requiring the radio to remain on for longer periods to ensure reception of the subsequent beacon.

config_element.name: unifiPrivateSWAGCExtThresh
config_element.description_user: Signal level at which external LNA will be used for AGC purposes.

config_element.name: unifiPrivateSWAGCFrontEndGain
config_element.description_user: Gain of the path between chip and antenna when LNA is on.

config_element.name: unifiPrivateSWAGCFrontEndLoss
config_element.description_user: Loss of the path between chip and antenna when LNA is off.

config_element.name: unifiChipVersion
config_element.description_user: Numeric identifier for the UniFi silicon revision (as returned by the GBL_CHIP_VERSION hardware register). Other than being different for each design variant (but not for alternative packaging options), the particular values returned do not have any significance.

config_element.name: unifiCrystalFrequencyTrim
config_element.description_user: The IEEE 802.11 standard requires a frequency accuracy of either +/- 20 ppm or +/- 25 ppm depending on the physical layer being used. If UniFi's frequency reference is a crystal then this attribute should be used to tweak the oscillating frequency to compensate for design- or device-specific variations. Each step change trims the frequency by approximately 2 ppm.

config_element.name: unifiDTIMWaitTimeout
config_element.description_user: If UniFi is in power save and receives a Traffic Indication Map from its associated access point with a DTIM indication, it will wait a maximum time given by this attribute for succeeding broadcast or multicast traffic, or until it receives such traffic with the 'more data' flag clear. Any reception of broadcast or multicast traffic with the 'more data' flag set, or any reception of unicast data, resets the timeout. The timeout can be turned off by setting the value to zero; in that case UniFi will remain awake indefinitely waiting for broadcast or multicast data. Otherwise, the value should be larger than that of unifiPowerSaveExtraListenTime.

config_element.name: unifiOutputRadioInfoToKernelLog
config_element.description_user: Print messages about the radio status to the Android Kernel Log. See document SC-508266-TC.

config_element.name: unifiDebugKeepRadioOn
config_element.description_user: Keep the radio on. For debug purposes only. Setting the value to FALSE means radio on/off functionality will behave normally. Note that setting this value to TRUE will automatically disable dorm. The intention is *not* for this value to be changed at runtime.

config_element.name: unifiForceFixedDurationSchedule
config_element.description_user: For schedules with fixed duration e.g. scan, unsync VIF, the schedule will be forced after this time to avoid VIF starving

config_element.name: unifiAntennaSelectionOption
config_element.description_user: Select how antennas will be allocated for SISO/RSDB/RSTB scenarios. Only valid for multi-radio platforms. WARNING: Changing this value after system start-up will have no effect. If the value is set to 0, antenna0 is used for 2G4 and antenna1 is used for 5G or 6G. If the value is set to 1, antenna1 is used for 2G4 and antenna0 is used for 5G or 6G. If the value is set to 2, the antenna with the strongest RSSI average will be preferred over the other antenna. Also see unifiAntennaSelection.

config_element.name: unifiSTAUsesOneAntennaWhenIdle
config_element.description_user: Allow the platform to downgrade antenna usage for STA VIFs to 1 if the VIF is idle. Only valid for multi-radio platforms.

config_element.name: unifiSTAUsesMultiAntennasDuringConnect
config_element.description_user: Allow the platform to use multiple antennas for STA VIFs during the connect phase. Only valid for multi-radio platforms.

config_element.name: unifiAPUsesOneAntennaWhenPeersIdle
config_element.description_user: Allow the platform to downgrade antenna usage for AP VIFs when all connected peers are idle. Only valid for multi-radio platforms.

config_element.name: deprecated_unifiUpdateAntennaCapabilitiesWhenScanning
config_element.description_user: Specify whether antenna scan activities will be allowed to cause an update of VIF capability. Only valid for multi-radio platforms. WARNING: Changing this value after system start-up will have no effect.

config_element.name: unifiPreferredAntennaBitmap
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Specify the preferred antenna(s) to use. A value of 0 means that the FW will decide on the antenna(s) to use. Only valid for multi-radio platforms. S630: - bit0 : RADIO_0_A (5G/6G) or RADIO_0_B(2G) - bit1 : RADIO_1_A(5G/6G) or RADIO_1_B(2G) S62x or earlier than S630: - bit0 : RADIO_0_A - bit1 : RADIO_1_A

config_element.name: unifiMaxConcurrentMACs
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Specify the maximum number of MACs that may be used for the platform. For multi-MAC platforms that value *could* be greater than 1. WARNING: Changing this value after system start-up will have no effect.

config_element.name: unifiMaxNumAntennaToUse
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Specify the maximum number of antenna that will be used for each band. Lower 8 bits = 2GHz, Mid 8 bits = 5Ghz, Higher 8 bits = 6Ghz. Limited by maximum supported by underlying hardware. WARNING: Changing this value after system start-up will have no effect.

config_element.name: unifiEnableTwoSimultaneousPassiveScansSameBand
config_element.description_user: Enable two passive scans to be simultaneously scheduled on two distinct channels at the same.

config_element.name: unifiSISOSwitchWaitTime
config_element.description_user: The amount of time in beacon intervals to evaluate whether an AP has responded correctly to a STA VIF attempting to switch from SISO to MIMO based on a host request. Only used if unifiHostNumAntennaControlActivated is set to true.

config_element.name: unifiEnableFlexiMacWatchdog
config_element.description_user: OBSOLETE. Bitmap controlling watchdog configuration for fleximac. Setting bit to 1 will enable watchdog for MAC represented by bit position

config_element.name: unifiEnableDorm
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Enable Dorm (deep sleep). When disabled, WLAN will not switch the radio power domain on/off *and* it will always veto deep sleep. Setting the value to TRUE means dorm functionality will behave normally. The intention is *not* for this value to be changed at runtime.

config_element.name: unifiTogglePowerDomain
config_element.description_user: Toggle WLAN power domain when entering dorm mode (deep sleep). When entering deep sleep and this value it true, then the WLAN power domain is disabled for the deep sleep duration. When false, the power domain is left turned on. This is to work around issues with WLAN rx, and is considered temporary until the root cause is found and fixed.

config_element.name: unifiDiscardedFrameCount
config_element.description_user: This is a counter that indicates the number of data and management frames that have been processed by the UniFi hardware but were discarded before being processed by the firmware. It does not include frames not processed by the hardware because they were not addressed to the local device, nor does it include frames discarded by the firmware in the course of normal MAC processing (which include, for example, frames in an appropriate encryption state and multicast frames not requested by the host). Typically this counter indicates lost data frames for which there was no buffer space; however, other cases may cause the counter to increment, such as receiving a retransmitted frame that was already successfully processed. Hence this counter should not be treated as a reliable guide to lost frames. The counter wraps to 0 after 65535.

config_element.name: unifiCurrentTSFTime
config_element.description_user: Get TSF time (last 32 bits) for the specified VIF. VIF index can't be 0 as that is treated as global VIF For station VIF - Correct BSS TSF wil only be reported after MLME-CONNECT.indication(success) indication to host. Note that if MAC Hardware is switched off then TSF returned is estimated value

config_element.name: unifiOffchannelProcedureTimeout
config_element.description_user: Maximum timeout in ms the Offchannel FSM will wait until the procedure is completed

config_element.name: unifiExtendedCapabilitiesSoftAp
config_element.description_user: Extended capabilities for SoftAp. Bit field definition and coding follows IEEE 802.11 Extended Capability Information Element, with spare subfields for capabilities that are independent from chip/firmware implementation.

config_element.name: unifiExtendedCapabilities
config_element.description_user: Extended capabilities. Bit field definition and coding follows IEEE 802.11 Extended Capability Information Element, with spare subfields for capabilities that are independent from chip/firmware implementation.

config_element.name: unifiExtendedCapabilitiesDisabled
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Suppress extended capabilities IE being sent in the association request. Please note that this may fix IOP issues with Aruba APs in WMMAC. Singed Decimal

config_element.name: unifiExternalClockDetect
config_element.description_user: If UniFi is running with an external fast clock source, i.e. unifiExternalFastClockRequest is set, it is common for this clock to be shared with other devices. Setting to true causes UniFi to detect when the clock is present (presumably in response to a request from another device), and to perform any pending activities at that time rather than requesting the clock again some time later. This is likely to reduce overall system power consumption by reducing the total time that the clock needs to be active.

config_element.name: unifiExternalFastClockRequest
config_element.description_user: It is possible to supply UniFi with an external fast reference clock, as an alternative to using a crystal. If such a clock is used then it is only required when UniFi is active. A signal can be output on PIO[2] or if the version of UniFi in use is the UF602x or later, any PIO may be used (see unifiExternalFastClockRequestPIO) to indicate when UniFi requires a fast clock. Setting makes this signal become active and determines the type of signal output. 0 - No clock request. 1 - Non inverted, totem pole. 2 - Inverted, totem pole. 3 - Open drain. 4 - Open source.

config_element.name: unifiExternalFastClockRequestPIO
config_element.description_user: If an external fast reference clock is being supplied to UniFi as an alternative to a crystal (see unifiExternalFastClockRequest) and the version of UniFi in use is the UF602x or later, any PIO may be used as the external fast clock request output from UniFi. key determines the PIO to use.

config_element.name: unifiDplaneTXAmsduHWCapability
config_element.description_user: Returns 0 if A-MSDU size limited to 4K. Returns 1 is A-MSDU size is limited to 8K. This value is chip specific and limited by HW.

config_element.name: unifiDplaneTXAmsduSubframeCountMax
config_element.description_user: Defines the maximum number of A-MSDU sub-frames per A-MSDU. A value of 1 indicates A-MSDU aggregation has been disabled

config_element.name: unifiAmsduSubframeRealtekOverrideActivated
config_element.description_user: When connected to Realtek chipset AP, inform Dataplane that actions need to be taken.

config_element.name: unifiHE40in5GRalinkOverrideEnable
config_element.description_user: When connected to Ralink chipset AP, inform MLME to override support of 40Mhz in 5G of HE phy capabilities when connected on 2.4G.

config_element.name: unifiDplaneTest1
config_element.description_user: Dplane test mib to read and write uint32

config_element.name: unifiDplaneTest2
config_element.description_user: Dplane test mib to read and write uint32

config_element.name: unifiDplaneTest3
config_element.description_user: Dplane test mib to read and write uint32

config_element.name: unifiDplaneTest4
config_element.description_user: Dplane test mib to read and write uint32

config_element.name: unifiEnableCopyPhyLogToDram
config_element.description_user: Enable or disable copying phy event logs in SRAM to DRAM

config_element.name: unifiDplaneDeafDetection
config_element.description_user: Configuration for Deaf detection algorithm. This feature only becomes enabled when it is FlexiMac and FM_DEAF_DETECTION flag is set. Usage: octet 0 - the number of consecutive cts without data frames to detect as deafness octet 1 - the number of consecutive rts without cts to detect as deafness octet 2 and 3 are not used 0 means disabling it.

config_element.name: unifiLiveRestartRssiThreshold
config_element.description_user: Minimum rssi threshold (dBm) to trigger live-restart If the RSSI is lower(poor) than this value, even if live-restart is requested by unifiDplaneDeafDetection, do not execute live-restart to avoid false alarm from environmental cause. This feature is disabled if set to 0 and only valid for STA VIFs.

config_element.name: unifiLiveRestartMinInterval
config_element.description_user: Minimum duration(ms) to execute live-restart from the previous restart. If elapsed time from previous live-restart is smaller than this value, even if live-restart is requested by unifiDplaneDeafDetection, do not execute live-restart to avoid redundant chatty alarm. This feature is disabled if set to 0.

config_element.name: unifiPhyEventLogEnable
config_element.description_user: Enable or Disable PHY Event Log - Disable: zero, Enable: None zero

config_element.name: unifiPhyEventToUDIConfig
config_element.description_user: Configure events that trigger sending PHY Event logs to UDI This feature is enabled when 1 is defined. Bitmap for configuring the trigger condition: 0x0000 : disabled 0x0001 : periodically 0x0002 : tx_failure 0x0004 : ba_missed 0x0008 : live_restart

config_element.name: unifiPhyEventToUDIInterval
config_element.description_user: Interval (milliseconds) to send PHY Event Logs to UDI Trigger condition is controlled by unifiPhyEventToUDIControl This feature is enabled when 1 is defined.

config_element.name: unifiPhyEventToUdiMinInterval
config_element.description_user: Minimal gap in msec from the last PHY Event Logs to UDI. PHY logs are generated only when the gap from the last logging is larger than MIB value.

config_element.name: unifiPhyEventToUdiMinBeaconMissInRow
config_element.description_user: Minimal beacon misses in a row to start PHY logging on beacon misses.

config_element.name: unifiMonitorStaAddress
config_element.description_user: MAC address of a target station to be captured in monitor (sniffer) mode. Monitor mode captures all received frames on a best-effort basis but there are certain frames which require pre-configuration before capturing. This feature will allow to capture HE-MU OFDMA frame by setting corresponding AID to the target station. Monitor vif uses this target station address to retrieve AID from AID-contained-frames automatically, e.g. assoc resp and NDPA.

config_element.name: unifiFastPowerSaveTimeout
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: UniFi implements a proprietary power management mode called Fast Power Save that balances network performance against power consumption. In this mode UniFi delays entering power save mode until it detects that there has been no exchange of data for the duration of time specified.

config_element.name: unifiFastPowerSaveTimeOutSmall
config_element.description_user: UniFi implements a proprietary power management mode called Fast Power Save that balances network performance against power consumption. In this mode UniFi delays entering power save mode until it detects that there has been no exchange of data for the duration of time specified. The unifiFastPowerSaveTimeOutSmall aims to improve the power consumption by setting a lower bound for the Fast Power Save Timeout. If set with a value above unifiFastPowerSaveTimeOut it will default to unifiFastPowerSaveTimeOut.

config_element.name: unifiFastPowerSaveTimeOutAggressive
config_element.description_user: UniFi implements a proprietary power management mode called Fast Power Save that balances network performance against power consumption. In this mode UniFi delays entering power save mode until it detects that there has been no exchange of data for the duration of time specified. The unifiFastPowerSaveTimeOutAggressive aims to improve the power consumption by setting a aggressive time when channel is not busy for the Fast Power Save Timeout. If set with a value above unifiFastPowerSaveTimeOut it will default to unifiFastPowerSaveTimeOut. Setting it to zero disables the feature

config_element.name: unifiDynamicITOEnable
config_element.description_user: Enables Dynamic ITO update feature

config_element.name: unifiDynamicITOControl
config_element.description_user: Control DynamicITO algorithm with bit flags. 1 defines enabled,with 0 showing the case disabled. bit 0: Dynamic ITO based on Beacon RX missed condition or struggling to receive beacons bit 1: Dynamic ITO based on Traffic condition (continuous or occasional) bit 2: Dynamic ITO based on Channel condition (Free/busy) bit 3: Dynamic ITO based on how fast AP responding to data

config_element.name: unifiRameDplaneOperationTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout for requests sent from MACRAME to Data Plane. Any value below 1000ms will be capped at 1000ms.

config_element.name: unifiVifIdleMonitorTime
config_element.description_user: In Fast Power Save mode, the STA will decide whether it is idle based on monitoring its traffic class. If the traffic class is continuously "occasional" for equal or longer than the specified value (in seconds), then the VIF is marked as idle. Traffic class monitoring is based on the interval specified in the "unifiTrafficAnalysisPeriod" MIB

config_element.name: unifiFirmwareBuildID
config_element.description_user: Numeric build identifier for this firmware build. This should normally be displayed in decimal. The textual build identifier is available via the standard dot11manufacturerProductVersion MIB attribute.

config_element.name: unifiFirmwarePatchBuildID
config_element.description_user: Numeric build identifier for the patch set that has been applied to this firmware image. This should normally be displayed in decimal. For a patched ROM build there will be two build identifiers, the first will correspond to the base ROM image, the second will correspond to the patch set that has been applied.

config_element.name: unifiDisallowSchedRelinquish
config_element.description_user: When enabled the VIFs will not relinquish their assigned schedules when they have nothing left to do.

config_element.name: unifiUspboTxAggregateBufferSize
config_element.description_user: Control BA TX agreements and Restrict the Tx BA Buffer size during non-LTE USPBO. 0 = Tx BA agreements will be suppressed during USPBO. 1 - 256 = Tx BA agreements will be preserved during USPBO, buffer size limited to this value. 0xffff = Tx BA agreements will be preserved during USPBO, buffer size limited to default value.

config_element.name: unifiMLMESTAKeepAliveFailure
config_element.description_user: Link lost by keep alive failure. 0 = Disabled. This is required by MCD. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiRestrictScoTxopSize
config_element.description_user: If non 0 value, during an SCO/ESCO USBPO, restrict the TXOP Limit to value (in steps of 32us). 0 = Do not restrict.

config_element.name: unifiMLMESTAKeepAliveTimeout
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Timeout before disconnecting in seconds. 0 = Disabled. Capped to greater than 6 seconds. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEAPKeepAliveTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout before disconnecting in seconds. 0 = Disabled. Capped to greater than 6 seconds. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEGOKeepAliveTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout before disconnecting in seconds. 0 = Disabled. Capped to greater than 6 seconds. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiMLMESTAKeepAliveTimeoutCheck
config_element.description_user: DO NOT SET TO A VALUE HIGHER THAN THE TIMEOUT. How long before keepalive timeout to start polling, in seconds. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEAPKeepAliveTimeoutCheck
config_element.description_user: DO NOT SET TO A VALUE HIGHER THAN THE TIMEOUT. How long before keepalive timeout to start polling, in seconds. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEGOKeepAliveTimeoutCheck
config_element.description_user: DO NOT SET TO A VALUE HIGHER THAN THE TIMEOUT. How long before keepalive timeout to start polling, in seconds. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiMLMESTAPktLifetime
config_element.description_user: MLME STA packet lifetime in seconds. Maximum time in seconds for a frame to be queued before sent out. This value is read only once when an interface is added. Used along with MlmeSendFrameRequest.

config_element.name: unifiSTARouterAdvertisementMinimumIntervalToForward
config_element.description_user: STA Mode: Minimum interval to forward Router Advertisement frames to Host. Minimum value = 60 secs.

config_element.name: unifiFragmentationDuration
config_element.description_user: A limit on transmission time for a data frame. If the data payload would take longer than unifiFragmentationDuration to transmit, UniFi will attempt to fragment the frame to ensure that the data portion of each fragment is within the limit. The limit imposed by the fragmentation threshold is also respected, and no more than 16 fragments may be generated. If the value is zero no limit is imposed. The value may be changed dynamically during connections. Note that the limit is a guideline and may not always be respected. In particular, the data rate is finalised after fragmentation in order to ensure responsiveness to conditions, the calculation is not performed to high accuracy, and octets added during encryption are not included in the duration calculation.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanMaxAerials
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name. Limit the number of Aerials that Scan will use.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanChannelRule
config_element.description_user: Rules for channel scanners.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanChannelMaxScanTime
config_element.description_user: Test only: overrides max_scan_time. 0 indicates not used.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanChannelProbeInterval
config_element.description_user: Test only: overrides probe interval. 0 indicates not used.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanDeltaRSSIThreshold
config_element.description_user: Magnitude of the change in RSSI for which a scan result will be issued. In dB.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanHighRSSIThreshold
config_element.description_user: Minimum RSSI, in dB, for a scan indication to be kept.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanMaximumResults
config_element.description_user: Max number of scan results, per sps, which will be stored before the oldest result is discarded, irrespective of its age. The value 0 specifies no maximum.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanDefaultShortFullScanTime
config_element.description_user: Scan channel duration when in short full scan mode.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanShortFullScanNumOfProbes
config_element.description_user: Number of probes for short full scan.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanContinueIfMoreThanXAps
config_element.description_user: Part of Scan Algorithm: Keep scanning on a channel with lots of APs.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanStopIfLessThanXNewAps
config_element.description_user: Part of Scan Algorithm: Stop scanning on a channel if less than X NEW APs are seen.

config_element.name: unifiScanMultiVifActivated
config_element.description_user: Part of Scan Algorithm: Activate support for Multi Vif channel times.

config_element.name: unifiScanNewAlgorithmActivated
config_element.description_user: Part of Scan Algorithm: Activate support for the new algorithm.

config_element.name: unifiScanRegisteredVIFInfrastructureSTA
config_element.description_user: Part of Scan Algorithm: Consider only Infrastructure STA vif as registered vif to choose VIF >= 1 scan parameters.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEScanStopIfLessThanXFrames
config_element.description_user: Stop scanning on a channel if less than X Beacons or Probe Responses are received.

config_element.name: unifiLowLatencyScanNProbe
config_element.description_user: Low Latency Scan: The number of ProbeRequest frames per channel.

config_element.name: unifiAPAssociationTimeout
config_element.description_user: SoftAP: Permitted time for a station to complete associatation with FW acting as AP in milliseconds.

config_element.name: unifiBSSMaxIdlePeriodActivated
config_element.description_user: If set STA will configure keep-alive with options specified in a received BSS max idle period IE

config_element.name: unifiBSSMaxIdlePeriod
config_element.description_user: BSS Idle MAX Period. Used to cap the value coming from BSS Max Idle Period IE, in seconds

config_element.name: unifiDmsActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate Directed Multicast Service (DMS)

config_element.name: unifiMLMEInactivityNewAlgorithmActivated
config_element.description_user: If enabled, the new algorithm which uses the timestamp of Sync frames (Beacon and Probe Response) would be used in logic to evaluate inactivity. If disabled, the old inactivity mechanism of any RX/TX timestamp and transmission of Null/QoS Null frame would be used in inactivity logic.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEStationInactivityTimeOut
config_element.description_user: Timeout, in seconds, for instigating ConnectonFailure procedures. Setting it to less than 3 seconds may result in frequent disconnection or roaming with the AP. Disable with Zero. Values lower than INACTIVITY_MINIMUM_TIMEOUT becomes INACTIVITY_MINIMUM_TIMEOUT. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiMLMECliInactivityTimeOut
config_element.description_user: Timeout, in seconds, for instigating ConnectonFailure procedures. Zero value disables the feature. Any value written lower than INACTIVITY_MINIMUM_TIMEOUT becomes INACTIVITY_MINIMUM_TIMEOUT. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEStationInitialKickTimeOut
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Timeout, in milliseconds, for sending the AP a NULL frame to kick off the EAPOL exchange. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiMLMEDataReferenceTimeout
config_element.description_user: Maximum time, in TU, allowed for the data in data references corresponding to MLME primitives to be made available to the firmware. The special value 0 specifies an infinite timeout.
config_element.description_internal: Note that the default has to be sufficient to allow for any MLME-SET.request used to set a different value! The value 65535 is reserved for future internal expansion (infinite timeout).

config_element.name: unifiPowerManagementDelayTimeout
config_element.description_user: When UniFi enters power save mode it signals the new state by setting the power management bit in the frame control field of a NULL frame. It then remains active for the period since the previous unicast reception, or since the transmission of the NULL frame, whichever is later. This entry controls the maximum time during which UniFi will continue to listen for data. This allows any buffered data on a remote device to be cleared. Specifies an upper limit on the timeout. UniFi internally implements a proprietary algorithm to adapt the timeout depending upon the situation.This is used by firmware when current station VIF is only station VIF which can be scheduled

config_element.name: unifiConcurrentPowerManagementDelayTimeout
config_element.description_user: When UniFi enters power save mode it signals the new state by setting the power management bit in the frame control field of a NULL frame. It then remains active for the period since the previous unicast reception, or since the transmission of the NULL frame, whichever is later. This entry controls the maximum time during which UniFi will continue to listen for data. This allows any buffered data on a remote device to be cleared. This is same as unifiPowerManagementDelayTimeout but this value is considered only when we are doing multivif operations and other VIFs are waiting to be scheduled.Note that firmware automatically chooses one of unifiPowerManagementDelayTimeout and unifiConcurrentPowerManagementDelayTimeout depending upon the current situation.It is sensible to set unifiPowerManagementDelayTimeout to be always more thanunifiConcurrentPowerManagementDelayTimeout.

config_element.name: unifiDisableLegacyPowerSave
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: This affects Station VIF power save behaviour. Setting it to true will disable legacy power save (i.e. we wil use fast power save to retrieve data) Note that actually disables full power save mode (i.e sending trigger to retrieve frames which will be PS-POLL for legacy and QOS-NULL for UAPSD)

config_element.name: unifiDebugForceActive
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Force station power save mode to be active (when scheduled). VIF scheduling, coex and other non-VIF specific reasons could still force power save on the VIF. Applies to all VIFs of type station (includes P2P client). Changes to the mib will only get applied after next host/mlme power management request.

config_element.name: unifiSupportMaxRequiredAntenna
config_element.description_user: Setting this MIB key to 'false' will use the number of antennas based on the peer device's advertised Nss. Setting this MIB key to 'true' will use the number of antennas based on the peers's max required antennas. An example where this is useful is when a peer advertises support for 1ss and STBC, thus 2 antennas must be used. For multi-antenna platforms only.

config_element.name: unifiMIFOffAllowed
config_element.description_user: Allow MIF to be turned off. If set to TRUE, it will prevent MIF to be turned off while WLAN is running. Disabling the mib will prevent to enter idle mode lite or idle mode medium

config_element.name: unifiMiflessStaEnable
config_element.description_user: This is flag for checking if MIFLESS for station vif is enabled or not. True means enabled. And false means disabled. This would be mainly depended on RF chip.

config_element.name: unifiMiflessAPBitmap
config_element.description_user: This is bitmap for checking if AP IDLE is MIFLESS of not BIT 0: Set means beacon is transmitted with MIF turned off.

config_element.name: unifiMiflessAPMinAwakeInterval
config_element.description_user: For Mifless AP low power mode this is the minimum time period in milliseconds before VIF re-enters low power mode after exiting due to DPHP RX

config_element.name: unifiAPIdleModeEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enables AP Idle mode if softAP is active, and there has been no activity for a time if unifiMiflessAPBitmap bit 0 is not set SOFTAP beacons will be transmitted with MIF turned on when IDLE otherwise beacon will be transmited in MIFLESS mode

config_element.name: unifiIdleModeLiteEnabled
config_element.description_user: DEPRECATED

config_element.name: unifiSTAIdleModeEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enables STA Idle mode, if single vif station is active and there has been no activity for a time.

config_element.name: unifiDualSTAIdleModeEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enables Dual STA Idle mode, if dual vif stations are active and both vifs are idle.

config_element.name: unifiSTAIdleModeControl
config_element.description_user: Control STA idle mode behaviour within firmware with bit flags. 1 defines enabled, 0 defines disabled. bit 0: STA idle mode with LCD on

config_element.name: unifiMacrameDebugStats
config_element.description_user: MACRAME debug stats readout key. Use set to write a debug readout, then read the same key to get the actual readout.

config_element.name: unifiSISOOnSingleNSSActivated
config_element.description_user: When activated, avoid MIMO+OMN and connect as SISO.

config_element.name: unifiARPDetectActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate feature support for Enhanced ARP Detect. This is required by Volcano.

config_element.name: unifiArpOutstandingMax
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of outstanding ARP frame transmissions in the firmware.

config_element.name: unifiRttCapabilities
config_element.description_user: RTT capabilities of the chip. see SC-506960-SW.

config_element.name: unifiFtmMinDeltaFrames
config_element.description_user: Default minimum time between consecutive FTM frames in units of 100 us.

config_element.name: unifiFtmPerBurst
config_element.description_user: Requested FTM frames per burst.

config_element.name: unifiFtmBurstDuration
config_element.description_user: indicates the duration of a burst instance, values 0, 1, 12-14 are reserved, [2..11], the burst duration is defined as (250 x 2)^(N-2), and 15 means "no preference".

config_element.name: unifiFtmNumOfBurstsExponent
config_element.description_user: The number of burst instances is 2^(Number of Bursts Exponent), value 15 means "no preference".

config_element.name: unifiFtmASAPModeActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate support for ASAP mode in FTM

config_element.name: unifiFtmResponderActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate support for FTM Responder

config_element.name: unifiFtmDefaultSessionEstablishmentTimeout
config_element.description_user: Default timeout for session estabishmant in units of ms.

config_element.name: unifiFtmDefaultGapBetweenBursts
config_element.description_user: Interval between consecutive Bursts. In units of ms.

config_element.name: unifiFtmDefaultTriggerDelay
config_element.description_user: Delay to account for differences in time between Initiator and Responder at start of the Burst. In units of ms.

config_element.name: unifiFtmDefaultEndBurstDelay
config_element.description_user: Delay to account for differences in time between Initiator and Responder at the end of the Burst. In units of ms.

config_element.name: unifiFtmRequestValidationEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enable Validation for FTM Add Range request RTT_Configs

config_element.name: unifiFtmResponseValidationEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enable Validation for FTM Response

config_element.name: unifiFtmUseResponseParameters
config_element.description_user: Use Response burst parameters for burst

config_element.name: unifiFtmInitialResponseTimeout
config_element.description_user: Default timeout for FtmInitialResponse in units of ms.

config_element.name: unifiFtmMacAddressRandomisation
config_element.description_user: Enable mac address randomisation for FTM initiator

config_element.name: unifiFtmUseRequestParameters
config_element.description_user: Use certain burst params from user while sending FTM req

config_element.name: unifiFtmMeanAroundCluster
config_element.description_user: Whether to get simple mean or mean around cluster

config_element.name: unifiFtm11azI2RLmrFeedback
config_element.description_user: I2R LMR Feedback ranging parameter in 11az IFTM request frame

config_element.name: unifiFtm11azSupport
config_element.description_user: Whether IEEE 802.11az FTM is supported

config_element.name: unifiFtm11azMinTimeBetweenMeasurements
config_element.description_user: This is a field in IEEE 802.11az FTM Ranging Non-TB specific sub element. In units of 100usec

config_element.name: unifiFtm11azMaxTimeBetweenMeasurements
config_element.description_user: This is a field in IEEE 802.11az FTM Ranging Non-TB specific sub element. In units of 10msec

config_element.name: unifiFtm11azTerminateSession
config_element.description_user: Whether IEEE 802.11az FTM Session has to be terminated or not

config_element.name: unifiFtm11azFormatBwRanging
config_element.description_user: 802.11az format bw and ranging parameter

config_element.name: unifiFtm11azImmediateR2I
config_element.description_user: 802.11az Immediate R2I parameter

config_element.name: unifiNANAllowCipherSuiteDowngrade
config_element.description_user: PRI-12398: Workaround for Framework not selecting correct Cipher Suite ID. FW would use Cipher Suite ID '1' if peer is using it even if Framework requested ID '2'.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxQueuedFollowups
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of NAN Followup instances which can be queued in FW.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxSDATxRetryCount
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of reties to send SDA to a peer.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxRangingRetryCount
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of retries FW does to perform a ranging (FTM burst sessions) and fails before terminating the ranging session. i.e. value of 4 will result in termination of ranging session after 5 consecutive ranging failure.

config_element.name: unifiNANSupportedCipherSuites
config_element.description_user: Set of supported cipher suites. NanCipherSuiteType bit field format.

config_element.name: unifiNANActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate Neighbour Aware Networking (NAN)

config_element.name: unifiNANRangingActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate Ranging Support.

config_element.name: unifiNANHeActivated
config_element.description_user: Enable HE mode for NAN.

config_element.name: unifiNANBeaconCapabilities
config_element.description_user: The 16-bit field follows the coding of IEEE 802.11 Capability Information.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxConcurrentClusters
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of concurrent NAN clusters supported.

config_element.name: unifiNanSkipNanChannelsIfNdlExists
config_element.description_user: Disable Nan Scan if an NDL exists.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxConcurrentPublishes
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of concurrent NAN Publish instances supported.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxConcurrentSubscribes
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of concurrent NAN Subscribe instances supported.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxConcurrentRangingAsInitiator
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of concurrent NAN Ranging Sessions supported as initiator.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxConcurrentRangingAsResponder
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of concurrent NAN Ranging Sessions supported as responder.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxServiceNameLength
config_element.description_user: Not used by FW. Maximum Service Name Length.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxMatchFilterLength
config_element.description_user: Not used by FW. Maximum Match Filter Length.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxTotalMatchFilterLength
config_element.description_user: Not used by FW. Maximum Total Match Filter Length.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxServiceSpecificInfoLength
config_element.description_user: Not used by FW. Maximum Service Specific Info Length.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxExtendedServiceSpecificInfoLen
config_element.description_user: Not used by FW. Maximum Extended Service Specific Info Length.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxSubscribeInterfaceAddresses
config_element.description_user: Not used by FW. Maximum number interface addresses in subscribe filter list.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxNDIInterfaces
config_element.description_user: Not used by FW. Maximum NDI Interfaces. Note: This does not affect number of NDL Vifs supported by FW as they are hard coded.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxNDPSessions
config_element.description_user: Not used by FW. Maximum NDP Sessions. Note: This does not affect number of NDP sessions supported by FW as they are hard coded.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxAppInfoLength
config_element.description_user: Not used by FW. Maximum App Info Length.

config_element.name: unifiNANMatchExpirationTime
config_element.description_user: Time limit in which Mlme will expire a match for discovered service. DW0 interval is 8s and all NAN devices shall be awake in DW0.

config_element.name: unifiNANPermittedChannels
config_element.description_user: Applicable Primary Channels mask. Defined in a uint64 represented by the octet string. Mapping defined in ChannelisationRules; i.e. Bit 14 maps to channel 36.

config_element.name: unifiNANDefaultScanPeriod
config_element.description_user: The default value of scan period in seconds.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxChannelSwitchTime
config_element.description_user: Maximum Channel Switch Time.

config_element.name: unifiNANMacRandomisationActivated
config_element.description_user: Enabling Mac Address Randomisation for NMI address.

config_element.name: uunifiNANDefaultScheduleTableIndex
config_element.description_user: NAN Schedule types.

config_element.name: unifiNANSchedulePreferenceIndex
config_element.description_user: NAN Schedule Preference.

config_element.name: unifiNANDefaultSchedule
config_element.description_user: Default Schedule to be proposed for NDL. FW will remove impossible / overlapping slots from proposal. Values must match with NAN Spec Time BitMap Control field values. Octet 0 ~ 1 : Ordered ChannelList[2] from most to least prefered channel, stated as channel number. Zero means not in used. Octet 2 : Bit Duration in TUs. Octet 3 ~ 4 : Period in TUs. Octet 5 ~ 6 : Start Offset in TUs. Octet 7 ~ 10 : TimeBitMap[4]

config_element.name: unifiNANKeepAliveTimeout
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name. Timeout before terminating in seconds. 0 = Disabled. Capped to greater than 6 seconds. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiNANKeepAliveTimeoutCheck
config_element.description_user: DO NOT SET TO A VALUE HIGHER THAN THE TIMEOUT. How long before keepalive timeout to start polling, in seconds. This value is read only once when an interface is added.

config_element.name: unifiNANDataPathTrafficTimeout
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name. Timeout before terminating NDP for no data traffic in seconds. 0 = Disabled.

config_element.name: unifiNANDataPathSetupTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout for a NDP setup.

config_element.name: unifiNANRangingSetupTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout for a Ranging setup.

config_element.name: unifiNANWarmupTimeout
config_element.description_user: Test MIB Only. Warmup time which FW doesn't set it's master preference. It's defined as 120s in spec.

config_element.name: unifiNanMultiVifSharedSlots
config_element.description_user: In multi vif scenarios, e.g. NAN + STA, NAN will share these slots with other VIFs. DW and NDC slots are not affected and are not removed due to MultiViF scenarios. Octet 0 : Bit Duration in TUs. Octet 1 ~ 2 : Period in TUs. Octet 3 ~ 4 : Start Offset in TUs. Octet 5 ~ 8 : TimeBitMap[4].

config_element.name: unifiRoamingInNDLActivated
config_element.description_user: When Activated, allow Roaming scan whilst NDL is active.

config_element.name: unifiNanMultiBandNdlPermitted
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name. When permitted, NDLs can use multi-band schedules.

config_element.name: unifiNanUlwTest
config_element.description_user: Deprecated.

config_element.name: unifiNanDiscoveryBeaconConfig
config_element.description_user: Enables NAN discovery beacon transmission for NMI vif. Setting/clearing bit 0 enables/disabled discovery beacons on 2GHz band. Setting/clearing bit 1 enables/disabled discovery beacons on 5GHz band. Setting/clearing bit 3 enables/disabled discovery beacons when theres an NDL vif on same band.

config_element.name: unifiNANForceWidestBandwidth
config_element.description_user: When Activated, schedules on NDL VIF with same primary channel will have same bandwidth equal to widest one.

config_element.name: unifiNANScanBoRepeatCount
config_element.description_user: The repeat count value to be used for blackouts installed for scan on NAN VIFs

config_element.name: unifiNANBlackoutFAWReductionActivated
config_element.description_user: When Activated, Blackouts aligned to FAWs with count == 255 are converted to FAW Reduction.

config_element.name: unifiNANTestMasterPreference
config_element.description_user: Test MIB for Master Preference value. This overwrites host value, and to take effect this MIB should be set before NAN start(FW reads this MIB on start and config request signals.).

config_element.name: unifiNANTestRangingDistance
config_element.description_user: Test MIB for Distance which Ranging reports. When this MIB is set, FW doesn't use FTM for ranging anymore.

config_element.name: unifiNANSDFTransmissionOutsideDWPermitted
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name. When this MIB is set FW is allowed to send SDF during remote CRB otherwise FW only sends SDF during DW.

config_element.name: unifiNANDeviceLinkSetupTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout for a NDL setup (re-negotiation).

config_element.name: unifiNANDeviceLinkScheduleUpdateRetryInterval
config_element.description_user: Retry interval of NDL renegotiation to fill empty slots. Set to zero for diabling retry.

config_element.name: unifiNanMultiVifDualBandConcurrencyPermitted
config_element.description_user: In multi vif scenarios, e.g. NAN + STA, NAN use RSDB, when possible, instead of time sharing with other VIFs.

config_element.name: unifiNANMaxNAFTxRetryCount
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of retries to send NAF(NDP Terminate at the moment.) to a peer.

config_element.name: unifiLowPowerRxConfig
config_element.description_user: Enables low power radio RX for idle STA and AP VIFs respectively. Setting/clearing bit 0 enables/disabled LP RX for (all) STA/Cli VIFs. Setting/clearing bit 1 enables/disabled LP RX for AP/GO VIFs.

config_element.name: unifiStationActivityIdleTime
config_element.description_user: Time since last station activity when it can be considered to be idle. Only used in SoftAP mode when determining if all connected stations are idle (not active).

config_element.name: unifiApBeaconMaxDrift
config_element.description_user: The maximum drift in microseconds we will allow for each beacon sent when we're trying to move it to get a 50% duty cycle between GO and STA in multiple VIF scenario. We'll delay our TX beacon by a maximum of this value until we reach our target TBTT. We have 3 possible cases for this value: a) ap_beacon_max_drift = 0x0000 - Feature disabled b) ap_beacon_max_drift between 0x0001 and 0xFFFE - Each time we transmit the beacon we'll move it a little bit forward but never more than this. (Not implemented yet) c) ap_beacon_max_drift = 0xFFFF - Move the beacon to the desired position in one shot.

config_element.name: unifiMacBeaconTimeout
config_element.description_user: The maximum time in microseconds we want to stall TX data when expecting a beacon at EBRT time as a station.

config_element.name: unifiRSSIMaxAveragingPeriod
config_element.description_user: Limits the period over which the value of unifiRSSI is averaged. If no more than unifiRSSIMinReceivedFrames frames have been received in the period, then the value of unifiRSSI is reset to the value of the next measurement and the rolling average is restarted. This ensures that the value is timely (although possibly poorly averaged) when little data is being received.

config_element.name: unifiRSSIMinReceivedFrames
config_element.description_user: See the description of unifiRSSIMaxAveragingPeriod for how the combination of attributes is used.

config_element.name: unifiCSROnlyEIFSDuration
config_element.description_user: Specifies time that is used for EIFS. A value of 0 causes the build in value to be used.

config_element.name: unifiForceChannelBW
config_element.description_user: Test only: Force channel bandwidth to specified value. This can also be used to allow emulator/silicon back to back connection to communicate at bandwidth other than default (20 MHz) Setting it to 0 uses the default bandwidth as selected by firmware. The change will be applied at next radio state change opportunity channel_bw_20_mhz = 20, channel_bw_40_mhz = 40, channel_bw_80_mhz = 80

config_element.name: unifiIqDebugEnabled
config_element.description_user: Send IQ capture data to host for IQ debug

config_element.name: unifiFtmOneCrossTwoSupport
config_element.description_user: Enable FTM 1*2 support

config_element.name: unifiSwToHwQueueStats
config_element.description_user: The timing statistics of packets being queued between SW-HW

config_element.name: unifiHostToSwQueueStats
config_element.description_user: The timing statistics of packets being queued between HOST-SW

config_element.name: unifiQueueStatsEnable
config_element.description_user: Enables recording timing statistics of packets being queued between HOST-SW-HW

config_element.name: unifiRateStatsRate
config_element.description_user: The rate corresponding to the current table entry. The value is rounded to the nearest number of units where necessary. Most rates do not require rounding, but when short guard interval is in effect the rates are no longer multiples of the base unit. Note that there may be two occurrences of the value 130: the first corresponds to MCS index 7, and the second, if present, to MCS index 6 with short guard interval.
config_element.description_internal: Get the rate for rate statistics table entry index.

config_element.name: unifiRateStatsRxSuccessCount
config_element.description_user: The number of successful receptions of complete management and data frames at the rate indexed by unifiRateStatsIndex.This number will wrap to zero after the range is exceeded.

config_element.name: unifiRateStatsTxSuccessCount
config_element.description_user: The number of successful (acknowledged) unicast transmissions of complete data or management frames the rate indexed by unifiRateStatsIndex. This number will wrap to zero after the range is exceeded.

config_element.name: unifiRateStatsRTSErrorCount
config_element.description_user: The number of successive RTS failures.

config_element.name: unifiTxDataConfirm
config_element.description_user: Allows to request on a per access class basis that an MA_UNITDATA.confirm be generated after each packet transfer. The default value is applied for all ACs.

config_element.name: unifiTxDataRate
config_element.description_user: The bit rate currently in use for transmissions of unicast data frames; On an infrastructure BSS, this is the data rate used in communicating with the associated access point, if there is none, an error is returned
config_element.description_internal: Request is made per-VIF. Rate is read from station records

config_element.name: unifiLastBssTxDataRate
config_element.description_user: Last BSS Tx DataRate. See unifiTxDataRate description.

config_element.name: unifiRSSITypeToUse
config_element.description_user: Define which type of RSSI averaging will be used internally, e.g. for determining roaming thresholds. If the value is set to 0, then the average RSSI for all frame types will be used. If the value is set to 1, then the maximum RSSI between the beacon-only and non-beacon-only averages will be used. If the value is set to 2, then the average RSSI for only beacon frame types will be used. Only used for VIFs of type STA. Also see unifiRSSIAvgType.

config_element.name: unifiNumRSSIAverageSample
config_element.description_user: The amount of samples used for calculating the average RSSI value. WARNING: Changing this value after system start-up will have no effect.

config_element.name: unifiRxDataRate
config_element.description_user: The bit rate of the last received frame on this VIF.
config_element.description_internal: Request is made per-VIF and only support for STA VIF type.

config_element.name: unifiNoAckActivationCount
config_element.description_user: The number of frames that are discarded due to HW No-ack activated during test. This number will wrap to zero after the range is exceeded.
config_element.description_internal: Number of discarded frames when HW No-ack is activated during test.

config_element.name: unifiRxFcsErrorCount
config_element.description_user: The number of received frames that are discarded due to bad FCS (CRC). This number will wrap to zero after the range is exceeded.
config_element.description_internal: Number of discarded received frames due to bad FCS (CRC) as detected by the HW.

config_element.name: unifiReadReg
config_element.description_user: Read value from a register and return it.
config_element.description_internal: Register access function.

config_element.name: unifiReadHardwareCounter
config_element.description_user: Read a value from a hardware packet counter for a specific radio_id and return it. The firmware will convert the radio_id to the associated mac_instance.
config_element.description_internal: Hardware counter access function.

config_element.name: unifiSwTxTimeout
config_element.description_user: Maximum time in seconds for a frame to be queued in firmware, ready to be sent, but not yet actually pumped to hardware.

config_element.name: unifiSNR
config_element.description_user: Provides a running average of the Signal to Noise Ratio (dB) for packets received by UniFi's radio.

config_element.name: unifiLastBssSNR
config_element.description_user: Last BSS SNR. See unifiSNR description.

config_element.name: unifiSNRExtraOffsetCCK
config_element.description_user: This offset is added to SNR values received at 802.11b data rates. This accounts for differences in the RF pathway between 802.11b and 802.11g demodulators. The offset applies to values of unifiSNR as well as SNR values in scan indications. Not used in 5GHz mode.

config_element.name: unifiScanMaxProbeTransmitLifetime
config_element.description_user: In TU. If non-zero, used during active scans as the maximum lifetime for probe requests. It is the elapsed time after the initial transmission at which further attempts to transmit the probe are terminated.

config_element.name: unifiProbeResponseLifetime
config_element.description_user: Lifetime of proberesponse frame in unit of ms.

config_element.name: unifiProbeResponseLifetimeP2P
config_element.description_user: Lifetime of proberesponse frame in unit of ms for P2P.

config_element.name: unifiProbeResponseMaxRetry
config_element.description_user: Number of retries of probe response frame.

config_element.name: unifiApDeauthTransmitLifetime
config_element.description_user: Lifetime of Deauth frame sent from AP in unit of ms.

config_element.name: unifiPowerSaveTransitionPacketThreshold
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name:If VIF has this many packets queued/transmitted/received in last unifiFastPowerSaveTransitionPeriod then firmware may decide to come out of aggressive power save mode. This is applicable to STA/CLI and AP/GO VIFs. Note that this is only a guideline. Firmware internal factors may override this MIB. Also see unifiTrafficAnalysisPeriod and unifiAggressivePowerSaveTransitionPeriod.

config_element.name: unifiTrafficAnalysisPeriod
config_element.description_user: Period in TUs over which firmware counts number of packet transmitted/queued/received to make decisions like coming out of aggressive power save mode or setting up BlockAck. This is applicable to STA/CLI and AP/GO VIFs. Note that this is only a guideline. Firmware internal factors may override this MIB. Also see unifiPowerSaveTransitionPacketThreshold, unifiAggressivePowerSaveTransitionPeriod and unifiTrafficThresholdToSetupBA.

config_element.name: unifiAggressivePowerSaveTransitionPeriod
config_element.description_user: Defines how many unifiTrafficAnalysisPeriod firmware should wait in which VIF had received/transmitted/queued less than unifiPowerSaveTransitionPacketThreshold packets - before entering aggressive power save mode (when not in aggressive power save mode) This is applicable to STA/CLI and AP/GO VIFs. Note that this is only a guideline. Firmware internal factors may override this MIB. Also see unifiPowerSaveTransitionPacketThreshold and unifiTrafficAnalysisPeriod.

config_element.name: unifiActiveTimeAfterMoreBit
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: After seeing the "more" bit set in a message from the AP, the STA will goto active mode for this duration of time. After this time, traffic information is evaluated to determine whether the STA should stay active or go to powersave. Setting this value to 0 means that the described functionality is disabled.

config_element.name: unifiMAXVifScheduleDuration
config_element.description_user: Default time for which a non-scan VIF can be scheduled. Applies to multiVIF scenario. Internal firmware logic or BSS state (e.g. NOA) may cut short the schedule.

config_element.name: unifiVifLongIntervalTime
config_element.description_user: When the scheduler expects a VIF to schedule for time longer than this parameter (specified in TUs), then the VIF may come out of powersave. Only valid for STA VIFs.

config_element.name: unifiUartConfigure
config_element.description_user: UART configuration using the values of the other unifiUart* attributes. The value supplied for this attribute is ignored.

config_element.name: unifiUartPios
config_element.description_user: Specification of which PIOs should be connected to the UART. Currently defined values are: 1 - UART not used; all PIOs are available for other uses. 2 - Data transmit and receive connected to PIO[12] and PIO[14] respectively. No hardware handshaking lines. 3 - Data and handshaking lines connected to PIO[12:15].

config_element.name: unifiWatchdogTimeout
config_element.description_user: Maximum time the background may be busy or locked out for. If this time is exceeded, UniFi will reset. If this key is set to 65535 then the watchdog will be disabled.

config_element.name: unifiLoggerEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enable reporting of the following events for Android logging: - firmware connectivity events - fate of management frames sent by the host through the MLME SAP It can take the following values: - 0: reporting for non mandetory triggers disabled. EAPOL, security, btm frames and roam triggers are reported. - 1: partial reporting is enabled. Beacons frames will not be reported. - 2: full reporting is enabled. Beacons frames are included.

config_element.name: unifiLoggerMaxDelayedEvents
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of events to keep when host is suspended.

config_element.name: unifiLoggerNANTrafficReportPeriod
config_element.description_user: Period in ms for sending NAN traffic updates to the host.

config_element.name: unifiRameUpdateMibs
config_element.description_user: Deprecated

config_element.name: unifiForceShortSlotTime
config_element.description_user: If set to true, forces FW to use short slot times for all VIFs.

config_element.name: unifiRSSI
config_element.description_user: Running average of the Received Signal Strength Indication (RSSI) for packets received by UniFi's radio. The value should only be treated as an indication of the signal strength; it is not an accurate measurement. The result is only meaningful if the unifiRxExternalGain attribute is set to the correct calibration value. If UniFi is part of a BSS, only frames originating from devices in the BSS are reported (so far as this can be determined). The average is reset when UniFi joins or starts a BSS or is reset.
config_element.description_internal: Use the lack of a (default) value to signal to rame that the RSSI hasn't been calibrated, and thus calls to mibgetrssi() will return FALSE.

config_element.name: unifiLastBssRSSI
config_element.description_user: Last BSS RSSI. See unifiRSSI description.

config_element.name: unifiBeaconCu
config_element.description_user: Provides a channel utilization of peer, value 255=100% channel utilization.

config_element.name: unifiPeerBandwidth
config_element.description_user: The bandwidth used with peer station prior it disconnects

config_element.name: unifiCurrentPeerNss
config_element.description_user: The number of spatial streams used with peer station prior it disconnects: BIG DATA

config_element.name: unifiPeerTxDataRate
config_element.description_user: The tx rate that was used for transmissions prior disconnection

config_element.name: unifiPeerRSSI
config_element.description_user: The recorded RSSI from peer station prior it disconnects

config_element.name: unifiPeerRxRetryCount
config_element.description_user: The number of retry packets from peer station

config_element.name: unifiPeerRxMulticastCount
config_element.description_user: The number of multicast and broadcast packets received from peer station

config_element.name: unifiAgcThresholds
config_element.description_user: AGC Thresholds settings

config_element.name: unifiTxSettings
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter settings

config_element.name: unifiTxGainSettings
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter gain settings

config_element.name: unifiTxPowerDetectorResponse
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter detector response settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxPowerDetectorResponseFrequency
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter detector response settings per frequency. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxDetectorTemperatureCompensation
config_element.description_user: Deprecated

config_element.name: unifiTxDetectorFrequencyCompensation
config_element.description_user: Deprecated

config_element.name: unifiTxOpenLoopTemperatureCompensation
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter open-loop temperature compensation settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxOpenLoopFrequencyCompensation
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter open-loop frequency compensation settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxPaGainDpdTemperatureCompensation
config_element.description_user: Deprecated

config_element.name: unifiTxPaGainDpdFrequencyCompensation
config_element.description_user: Deprecated

config_element.name: unifiTxFtrimSettings
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter frequency compensation settings

config_element.name: unifiTxGainStepSettings
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter gain step settings. 2G settings before 5G. Increasing order within band.

config_element.name: unifiTxOfdmSelect
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter OFDM selection settings

config_element.name: unifiTxDigGain
config_element.description_user: Specify gain specific modulation power optimisation.

config_element.name: unifiStaticDpdGain
config_element.description_user: Specify modulation specifc gains for static dpd optimisation.

config_element.name: unifiChipTemperature
config_element.description_user: Read the chip temperature as seen by WLAN radio firmware.

config_element.name: unifiChipTemperatureDirect
config_element.description_user: Read the chip current temperature by sending a reading request to the RF chip and waits for value to return.

config_element.name: UnifiBatteryVoltage
config_element.description_user: Battery voltage

config_element.name: unifiLoadDpdLut
config_element.description_user: Write a static DPD LUT to the FW, read DPD LUT from hardware
config_element.description_internal: the set function writes static dpd lut values from hcf into firmware, the get function reads from hardware

config_element.name: unifiOverrideDpdLut
config_element.description_user: Write a DPD LUT directly to the HW
config_element.description_internal: Used for Matlab characterisation by writing a previously calculated and (possibly) smoothed LUT to the HW. The primary need for this is because writing the LUT directly in Matlab is very slow and hence impractical for any characterisation work.

config_element.name: unifiLoadDpdLutPerRadio
config_element.description_user: Write a static DPD LUT to the FW, read DPD LUT from hardware (for devices that support multiple radios)
config_element.description_internal: the set function writes static dpd lut values from hcf into firmware, the get function reads from hardware

config_element.name: unifiOverrideDpdLutPerRadio
config_element.description_user: Write a DPD LUT directly to the HW (for devices that support multiple radios)
config_element.description_internal: Used for Matlab characterisation by writing a previously calculated and (possibly) smoothed LUT to the HW. The primary need for this is because writing the LUT directly in Matlab is very slow and hence impractical for any characterisation work.

config_element.name: unifiLoadMemDpdLut
config_element.description_user: Write a static DPD LUT to the FW, read DPD LUT from hardware for devices that support Memory DPD
config_element.description_internal: the set function writes static dpd lut values from hcf into firmware, the get function reads from hardware

config_element.name: unifiOverrideMemDpdLut
config_element.description_user: Write a DPD LUT directly to the HW for devices that support Memory DPD
config_element.description_internal: Used for Matlab characterisation by writing a previously calculated and (possibly) smoothed LUT to the HW. The primary need for this is because writing the LUT directly in Matlab is very slow and hence impractical for any characterisation work.

config_element.name: unifiDpdPredistortGains
config_element.description_user: DPD pre-distort gains. Takes a range of frequencies, where f_min <= f_channel < f_max. The format is [freq_min_msb, freq_min_lsb, freq_max_msb, freq_max_lsb, DPD policy bitmap, bandwidth_bitmap, power_trim_enable, OFDM0_gain, OFDM1_gain, CCK_gain, TR_gain, CCK PSAT gain, OFDM PSAT gain].

config_element.name: unifiDpdMasterSwitch
config_element.description_user: Enables Digital Pre-Distortion
config_element.description_internal: Bitmask of DPD features to enable for testing, requires d01_d01 or later.

config_element.name: unifiCCAMasterSwitch
config_element.description_user: Enables CCA
config_element.description_internal: Bitmask of CCA features to enable. Note MIB is not live, value will get loaded to hardware after radio is switched on. The least significant word is for config of ETSI regulatory domain 80Mhz p0 and p4, the other word is for all other configurations.

config_element.name: unifiRxSyncCCACfg
config_element.description_user: Configures CCA per 20 MHz sub-band.
config_element.description_internal: Configure to take into account the CCA of each 20M subband for the primary channel.

config_element.name: unifiFleximacCcaEdEnable
config_element.description_user: Enable/disable CCA-ED in Fleximac.

config_element.name: unifiMacCCABusyTime
config_element.description_user: Counts the time CCA indicates busy
config_element.description_internal: This register counts the time CCA indicates busy (for pri20/sec20 and sec40), in units of 16 us.

config_element.name: unifiMacSecChanClearTime
config_element.description_user: Configures PIFS
config_element.description_internal: Secondary Channel must be free for this amount of time (50ns unit) before it is declared non-busy for starting a Txop. Related to PIFS.

config_element.name: unifiDpdDebug
config_element.description_user: Debug MIBs for DPD

config_element.name: unifiCCACSThresh
config_element.description_user: Configures CCA CS thresholds.
config_element.description_internal: Configures CCA CS (packet sync) thresholds. Indexed by siso/mimo.

config_element.name: unifiCoexDebugOverrideBt
config_element.description_user: Enables overriding of all BT activities by WLAN.
config_element.description_internal: When this MIB is set then no macrame blackouts are registered for any BT activities and also WLAN trumps all BT activities at the HW CDL arbitration level. This MIB should be enabled only for debugging purposes. This MIB will only have an effect when its either compiled into the FW image or is configured at WLAN boot via an hcf file.

config_element.name: unifiTxPowerTrimConfig
config_element.description_user: Hardware specific transmitter power trim settings
config_element.description_internal: Configuration settings for the TX power trim. The format depends on the RFIC. S630 (18 octets): [rf_chip_bitmap_lso, rf_chip_bitmap_mso radio_id, band, psat_dig_gain, psat_bb_stg1_rfb, psat_bb_stg2_rin, psat_bb_stg2_rfb, psat_bb_stg2_rin_teg, psat_mix_slice, psat_drv_slice, psat_drv_gain_sel, psat_iptat_main, psat_iref_cas, psat_iref_main, psat_epa_gain_idx, psat_power_ref_mso, psat_power_ref_lso] S62x (26 octets): [rf_chip_bitmap_lso, rf_chip_bitmap_mso radio_id, band, pcal_ofdm0_to_cck_mso, pcal_ofdm0_to_cck_lso, pcal_ofdm0_to_ofdm1_mso, pcal_ofdm0_to_ofdm1_lso, pcal_20_to_80_mso, pcal_20_to_80_lso, pcal_20_to_40_mso, pcal_20_to_40_lso, psat_dig_gain, psat_v2i_gain, psat_mix_gain, psat_drv_gain, psat_pa_gain, psat_power_ref_mso, psat_power_ref_lso, psat_drv_bias, psat_pa_bias, spare, spare, spare, spare].

config_element.name: unifiTxPowerTrimCommonConfig
config_element.description_user: Common transmitter power trim settings
config_element.description_internal: Common configuration settings for the TX power trim

config_element.name: unifiClearRadioTrimCache
