config_element.description_user:
Override the AGC by adjusting the Rx minimum and maximum gains of each stage. Set requests write the values to a static structure in firmware. The saved values are written to hardware, and also used to configure the AGC whenever halradio_agc_setup() is called. Get requests read the values from the static structure in firmware. AGC enables are not altered. Fixed gain may be tested by setting the minimums and maximums to the same value.
Version 1 (for rfchip jar - not supported on this firmware branch) octet 0 - Version number = 1. Gain values. Default in brackets. octet 1 - 5G LNA minimum gain (0). octet 2 - 5G LNA maximum gain (4). octet 3 - 2G LNA minimum gain (0). octet 4 - 2G LNA maximum gain (5). octet 5 - Mixer minimum gain (0). octet 6 - Mixer maximum gain (2). octet 7 - ABB minimum gain (8). octet 8 - ABB maximum gain (27). octet 9 - Digital minimum gain (depends on bb chip). octet 10 - Digital maximum gain (depends on bb chip).
Version 2 (for rfchip hopper, lark) octet 0 - Version number = 2. Gain values. Default in brackets. octet 1 - 5G FE minimum gain (hopper 1, lark 0). octet 2 - 5G FE maximum gain (8). octet 3 - 2G FE minimum gain (0). octet 4 - 2G FE maximum gain (8). octet 5 - ABB minimum gain (1). octet 6 - ABB maximum gain (9). octet 7 - Digital minimum gain (depends on bb chip). octet 8 - Digital maximum gain (depends on bb chip).
Version 3 (for rfchip leopard with 6G compatible and ax capable BBIC) octet 0 - Version number = 3. Gain values. Default in brackets. octet 1 - 6G FE minimum gain (0). octet 2 - 6G FE maximum gain (8). octet 3 - 5G FE minimum gain (0). octet 4 - 5G FE maximum gain (8). octet 5 - 2G FE minimum gain (0). octet 6 - 2G FE maximum gain (8). octet 7 - ABB minimum gain (1). octet 8 - ABB maximum gain (9). octet 9 - Digital minimum gain (depends on bb chip). octet 10 - Digital maximum gain (depends on bb chip).

config_element.name: unifiSableContainerSizeConfiguration
config_element.description_user: Sable Container Size Configuration Sable WLAN reserved memory size is determined by the host. Sable TLV containers are allocated from this WLAN reserved area. Each container has different requirement on its size. For example, frame logging or IQ capture would be very greedy, requesting most of available memroy. But some just need fixed size, but not large. To cope with such requirements, each container size is configured with the following rules: 1. To allocate a certain percentage of the whole wlan reserved area, put the percentage in hex format. For example, 0x28(=40) means 40% of reserved area will be assigned. The number 0x64(=100) is specially treated that all remaining space will be assigned after all the other containers are first served. 2. To request (n * 2048) bytes, put (100 + n) value in hex format. For example, 0x96 (= 150) means 50 * 2048 = 102400 bytes. Here are the list of containers: - octet 0 - WTLV_CONTAINER_ID_DPLANE_FRAME_LOG

config_element.description_user: If a valid Setup Response frame is not received within (seconds), the initiator STA shall terminate the setup procedure and discard any Setup Response frames.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsActivated
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Activate TDLS.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsInP2pActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate TDLS in P2P.

config_element.name: unifiMaxTDLSClient
config_element.description_user: Maximum number of clients Supported in TDLS.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsWiderBandwidthProhibited
config_element.description_user: Wider bandwidth prohibited flag.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsTPThresholdPktSecs
config_element.description_user: Used for "throughput_threshold_pktsecs" of RAME-MLME-ENABLE-PEER-TRAFFIC-REPORTING.request.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsRssiThreshold
config_element.description_user: FW initiated TDLS Discovery/Setup procedure. If the RSSI of a received TDLS Discovery Response frame is greater than this value, initiate the TDLS Setup procedure.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsTPMonitorSecs
config_element.description_user: Measurement period for recording the number of packets sent to a peer over a TDLS link.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsKeyLifeTimeInterval
config_element.description_user: Build the Key Lifetime Interval in the TDLS Setup Request frame.

config_element.name: unifiTdlsTeardownFrameTxTimeout
config_element.description_user: Allowed time in milliseconds for a Teardown frame to be transmitted.

config_element.name: unifiWifiSharingActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate WiFi Sharing feature

config_element.name: unifiWiFiSharingChannels
config_element.description_user: Default host allowed channels during Wifi Sharing. Defined in a uint64 represented by the octet string. First byte of the octet string maps to LSB. Bits 0-13 representing 2.4G channels. Mapping defined in ChannelisationRules.

config_element.name: unifiWiFiSharing5GHzChannel
config_element.description_user: Deprecated. Applicable 5GHz Primary Channels mask. Defined in a uint64 represented by the octet string. First byte of the octet string maps to LSB. Bits 0-13 representing 2.4G channels are always set to 0. Mapping defined in ChannelisationRules; i.e. Bit 14 maps to channel 36.

config_element.name: unifiWifiSharingChannelSwitchCount
config_element.description_user: Channel switch announcement count which will be used in the Channel announcement IE when using wifi sharing

config_element.name: unifiChannelAnnouncementCount
config_element.description_user: Channel switch announcement count which will be used in the Channel announcement IE

config_element.name: unifiStaChannelSwitchSlowApActivated
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: ChanelSwitch: Activate waiting for a slow AP.

config_element.name: unifiStaChannelSwitchSlowApMaxTime
config_element.description_user: ChannelSwitch delay for Slow APs. In Seconds.

config_element.name: unifiStaChannelSwitchSlowApPollInterval
config_element.description_user: ChannelSwitch polling interval for Slow APs. In Seconds.

config_element.name: unifiStaChannelSwitchSlowApProcedureTimeoutIncrement
config_element.description_user: ChannelSwitch procedure timeout increment for Slow APs. In Seconds.

config_element.name: unifiRATestStoredSA
config_element.description_user: Test only: Source address of router contained in virtural router advertisement packet, specified in chapter '6.2 Forward Received RA frame to Host' in SC-506393-TE

config_element.name: unifiRATestStoreFrame
config_element.description_user: Test only: Virtual router advertisement packet. Specified in chapter '6.2 Forward Received RA frame to Host' in SC-506393-TE

config_element.name: unifiSupportedChannels
config_element.description_user: For Test Only. Supported 20MHz channel primary frequency grouped in sub-bands. For each sub-band: starting channel number, followed by number of channels.

config_element.name: unifiDefaultCountry
config_element.description_user: Deprecated. Host set Default Code.

config_element.name: unifiDefaultCountryWithoutCH12CH13
config_element.description_user: Update the default country code to ensure CH12 and CH13 are not used.

config_element.name: unifiCountryList
config_element.description_user: Deprecated. Defines the ordered list of countries present in unifiRegulatoryTable. Each country is coded as 2 ASCII characters. If unifiRegulatoryTable is modified, such as a country is either added, deleted or its relative location is modified, has to be updated as well.

config_element.name: unifiVifCountry
config_element.description_user: Per VIf: Each VIF updates its Country Code for the Host to read

config_element.name: unifiStationQosInfo
config_element.description_user: QoS capability for a non-AP Station, and is encoded as per IEEE 802.11 QoS Capability.

config_element.name: unifiBeaconSkippingControl
config_element.description_user: Control beacon skipping behaviour within firmware with bit flags. 1 defines enabled, with 0 showing the case disabled. If beacon skipping is enabled, further determine if DTIM beacons can be skipped, or only non-DTIM beacons. The following applies: bit 0: station skipping on host suspend bit 1: station skipping on host awake bit 2: station skipping on LCD on bit 3: station skipping with multivif bit 4: station skipping with BT active. bit 8: station skip dtim on host suspend bit 9: station skip dtim on host awake bit 10: station skip dtim on LCD on bit 11: station skip dtim on multivif bit 12: station skip dtim with BT active bit 16: p2p-gc skipping on host suspend bit 17: p2p-gc skipping on host awake bit 18: p2p-gc skipping on LCD on bit 19: p2p-gc skipping with multivif bit 20: p2p-gc skipping with BT active bit 24: p2p-gc skip dtim on host suspend bit 25: p2p-gc skip dtim on host awake bit 26: p2p-gc skip dtim on LCD on bit 27: p2p-gc skip dtim on multivif bit 28: p2p-gc skip dtim with BT active

config_element.name: unifiListenIntervalSkippingDTIM
config_element.description_user: Listen interval of beacons when in single-vif power saving mode,receiving DTIMs is enabled and idle mode disabled. No DTIMs are skipped during MVIF operation. A maximum of the listen interval beacons are skipped, which may be less than the number of DTIMs that can be skipped. The value is a lookup table for DTIM counts. Each 4bits, in LSB order, represent DTIM1, DTIM2, DTIM3, DTIM4, DTIM5, (unused). This key is only used for STA VIF, connected to an AP. For P2P group client intervals, refer to unifiP2PListenIntervalSkippingDTIM, PSID=2523.

config_element.name: unifiP2PListenIntervalSkippingDTIM
config_element.description_user: Listen interval of beacons when in single-vif, P2P client power saving mode,receiving DTIMs and idle mode disabled. No DTIMs are skipped during MVIF operation. A maximum of (listen interval - 1) beacons are skipped, which may be less than the number of DTIMs that can be skipped. The value is a lookup table for DTIM counts. Each 4bits, in LSB order, represent DTIM1, DTIM2, DTIM3, DTIM4, DTIM5, (unused). This key is only used for P2P group client. For STA connected to an AP, refer to unifiListenIntervalSkippingDTIM, PSID=2518.

config_element.name: unifiIdlemodeListenIntervalSkippingDTIM
config_element.description_user: Listen interval of beacons when in single-vif power saving mode, receiving DTIMs is enabled and idle mode enabled. No DTIMs are skipped during MVIF operation. A maximum of the listen interval beacons are skipped, which may be less than the number of DTIMs that can be skipped. The value is a lookup table for DTIM counts. Each 4bits, in LSB order, represent DTIM1, DTIM2, DTIM3, DTIM4, DTIM5, (unused). This key is only used for STA VIF, connected to an AP. For P2P group client intervals, refer to unifiIdlemodeP2PListenIntervalSkippingDTIM, PSID=2496.

config_element.name: unifiIdlemodeP2PListenIntervalSkippingDTIM
config_element.description_user: Listen interval of beacons when in single-vif, P2P client power saving mode,receiving DTIMs and idle mode enabled. No DTIMs are skipped during MVIF operation. A maximum of (listen interval - 1) beacons are skipped, which may be less than the number of DTIMs that can be skipped. The value is a lookup table for DTIM counts. Each 4bits, in LSB order, represent DTIM1, DTIM2, DTIM3, DTIM4, DTIM5, (unused). This key is only used for P2P group client. For STA connected to an AP, refer to unifiIdlemodeListenIntervalSkippingDTIM, PSID=2495.

config_element.name: unifiListenIntervalMaxTime
config_element.description_user: Maximum number length of time, in Time Units (1TU = 1024us), that can be used as a beacon listen interval. This will limit how many beacons maybe skipped, and affects the DTIM beacon skipping count; DTIM skipping (if enabled) will be such that skipped count = (unifiListenIntervalMaxTime / DTIM_period).

config_element.name: unifiUseHostListenInterval
config_element.description_user: Listen interval of beacons when in single-vif as set by host.

config_element.name: unifiListenInterval
config_element.description_user: Association request listen interval parameter in beacon intervals. Not used for any other purpose.

config_element.name: unifiBeaconsReceivedPercentage
config_element.description_user: Percentage of beacons received, calculated as received / expected. The percentage is scaled to an integer value between 0 (0%) and 1000 (100%).

config_element.name: unifiMaxBeaconListenWindowTime
config_element.description_user: The maximum beacon listen window time we can limit on.This is the difference between listen end and listen start time.

config_element.name: unifiBeaconRXPeriodUpdate
config_element.description_user: Enables beacon rx period update, if AP is sending wrong beacon period.

config_element.name: unifiHtCapabilities
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name. HT capabilities of the chip. See SC-503520-SP for further details. NOTE: Greenfield has been disabled due to interoperability issues wuth SGI.

config_element.name: unifiHtCapabilitiesSoftAp
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name. HT capabilities for softAP to disallow MIMO when customer want to control MIMO/ SISO mode (see SC-508764-DD for further details). NOTE: Greenfield has been disabled due to interoperability issues with setting SGI.

config_element.name: unifiVhtCapabilities
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name. VHT capabilities of the chip. see SC-503520-SP.

config_element.name: unifiHtApDowngradeByNSSActivated
config_element.description_user: Enable HT Ap downgrade when NSS is changed. This is customer specific.

config_element.name: unifiSuppressSTSUpdateBasedOnPeer
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Do not update STS in VHT caps based on Peer's sounding dimensions.

config_element.name: unifiFrameResponseTimeOut
config_element.description_user: Timeout, in TU, to wait for a frame(Auth, Assoc, ReAssoc) after TX Cfm trasnmission_status == Successful.

config_element.name: unifiFrameResponseLongTimeOut
config_element.description_user: Deprecated. Timeout, in TU, to wait for a frame(Auth, Assoc, ReAssoc) after TX Cfm trasnmission_status == Successful for SAE

config_element.name: unifiFrameResponseNdmTimeOut
config_element.description_user: Timeout, in TU, to wait to retry a frame after after TX Cfm trasnmission_status == Successful.

config_element.name: unifiFrameResponseCfmFailureTimeOut
config_element.description_user: Timeout, in TU, to wait to retry a frame after TX Cfm trasnmission_status != Successful.

config_element.name: unifiInitialConnectionFailureTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout, in TU, for a frame retry before giving up for initial connection.

config_element.name: unifRetryAuthForSpecialAps
config_element.description_user: How long, in milliseconds, before ConnectionFailureTimeout to send authentication frame for special aps.

config_element.name: unifiConnectionFailureTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout, in TU, for a frame retry before giving up.

config_element.name: unifiAssocComebackTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout, in TU, for a association comeback limit before giving up.

config_element.name: unifiConnectingProbeTimeout
config_element.description_user: How long, in TU, to wait for a ProbeRsp when syncronising before resending a ProbeReq

config_element.name: unifiDisconnectTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout, in milliseconds, to perform a disconnect or disconnect all STAs (triggered by MLME_DISCONNECT-REQ or MLME_DISCONNECT-REQ 00:00:00:00:00:00) before responding with MLME-DISCONNECT-IND and aborting the disconnection attempt. This is particulary important when a SoftAP is attempting to disconnect associated stations which might have "silently" left the ESS.

config_element.name: unifiAutoConnectionTestActivated
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete. Enable auto response for connection without radio

config_element.name: unifiAutoConnectionTestBSSID
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete. Select the BSSID for the AP when auto response is enabled

config_element.name: unifiForceActiveDuration
config_element.description_user: How long, in milliseconds, the firmware temporarily extends PowerSave for STA as a workaround for wonky APs such as D-link.

config_element.name: unifiBaTxEnableTid
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Configure Block Ack TX on a per-TID basis. Bit mask is two bits per TID (B1 = autosetup, B0 = enable).

config_element.name: unifiBaRxEnableTid
config_element.description_user: Configure Block Ack RX on a per-TID basis. Bit mask is two bits per TID (B1 = Not Used, B0 = enable).

config_element.name: unifiBaConfig
config_element.description_user: Block Ack Configuration. It is composed of A-MSDU supported, TX MPDU per A-MPDU, RX Buffer size, TX Buffer size and Block Ack Timeout. Indexed by unifiAccessClassIndex.

config_element.name: unifiBaTxMaxNumber
config_element.description_user: Block Ack Configuration. Maximum number of BAs. Limited by HW.

config_element.name: unifiBaRxInternalDeleteDisabled
config_element.description_user: Disable Rx Block Ack from being deleted internally. The BA delete is still advertised to the peer, but is not deleted internally. This is applicable only when the delete does not come from the peer.

config_element.name: unifiMoveBKtoBE
config_element.description_user: Deprecated. Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name

config_element.name: unifiRoamBaWinSize
config_element.description_user: Block Ack Configuration. Maximum number of BAs for receiving a-mpdu frame. Limited by HW.

config_element.name: unifiRoamMPDUSS
config_element.description_user: minimum MPDU start spacing of the MPDUs receiver. Limited by HW.

config_element.name: unifiRoamETEActivated
config_element.description_user: This MIB activates support for calculation of estimated throughput. This sorts all candidates by descending order of the throughput.

config_element.name: unifiSupportedDataRates
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Defines the supported non-HT data rates. It is encoded as N+1 octets where the first octet is N and the subsequent octets each describe a single supported rate.

config_element.name: unifiDualBandConcurrency
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name. Identify whether the chip supports dualband concurrency or not (RSDB vs. VSDB). Set in the respective platform htf file.

config_element.name: unifiApOlbcDuration
config_element.description_user: How long, in milliseconds, the AP enables reception of BEACON frames to perform Overlapping Legacy BSS Condition(OLBC). If set to 0 then OLBC is disabled.

config_element.name: unifiApOlbcInterval
config_element.description_user: How long, in milliseconds, between periods of receiving BEACON frames to perform Overlapping Legacy BSS Condition(OLBC). This value MUST exceed the OBLC duration MIB unifiApOlbcDuration. If set to 0 then OLBC is disabled.

config_element.name: unifiDNSSupportActivated
config_element.description_user: This MIB activates support for transmitting DNS frame via MLME.

config_element.name: unifiIgmpOffloadActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate IGMP IPv4 Offloading.

config_element.name: unifiMaxClient
config_element.description_user: Restricts the maximum number of associated STAs for SoftAP.

config_element.name: unifiPMFAssociationComebackTimeDelta
config_element.description_user: Timeout interval, in TU, for the TimeOut IE in the SA Query request frame.

config_element.name: unifiDefaultDwellTime
config_element.description_user: Dwell time for frames that need a response but have no dwell time associated.

config_element.name: unifiSAEDwellTime
config_element.description_user: Dwell time for SAE Auth frames.

config_element.name: unifiGOScanAbsenceDuration
config_element.description_user: Duration of the Absence time to use when protecting P2PGO VIFs from scan operations. A value of 0 disables the feature.

config_element.name: unifiGOScanAbsencePeriod
config_element.description_user: Period of the Absence/Presence times cycles to use when protecting P2PGO VIFs from scan operations.

config_element.name: unifiAPScanAbsenceDuration
config_element.description_user: Duration of the Absence time to use when protecting AP VIFs from scan operations. A value of 0 disables the feature.

config_element.name: unifiAPScanAbsencePeriod
config_element.description_user: Period of the Absence/Presence times cycles to use when protecting AP VIFs from scan operations.

config_element.name: unifiGOCTWindowDuration
config_element.description_user: Client Traffic Window in TU to be set for oppertunistic power save in P2PGO.This will help reduce the GO power consumption but may adversly affect P2PGO disconverability.

config_element.name: unifiSuppressScanGONoaAnnounce
config_element.description_user: Stop a p2p GO from sending NoA announcements when the GO needs to be absent for scanning purposes.

config_element.name: unifiGOCTWindowDelay
config_element.description_user: Delay to apply Client Traffic Window in seconds for oppertunistic power save in P2PGO.

config_element.name: unifiVhtActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate VHT mode.

config_element.name: unifiTqamActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate Vendor VHT IE for 256-QAM mode on 2.4GHz.

config_element.name: unifiHtActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate HT mode.

config_element.name: unifiWipsActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate Wips.

config_element.name: unifiSoftAp40MHzOn24G
config_element.description_user: Enables 40MHz operation on 2.4GHz band for SoftAP.

config_element.name: unifi24G40MHZChannels
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Enables 40Mz wide channels in the 2.4G band for STA. This can only be changed before STA is coonected.

config_element.name: unifiTxUsingLdpcActivated
config_element.description_user: LDPC will be used to code packets, for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not send LDPC coded packets even if peer supports it. To advertise reception of LDPC coded packets,enable bit 0 of unifiHtCapabilities, and bit 4 of unifiVhtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiTxSGI20Activated
config_element.description_user: SGI 20MHz will be used to code packets for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not send SGI 20MHz packets even if peer supports it. To advertise reception of SGI 20MHz packets, enable bit 5 of unifiHtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiTxSGI40Activated
config_element.description_user: SGI 40MHz will be used to code packets, for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not send SGI 40MHz packets even if peer supports it. To advertise reception of SGI 40MHz packets, enable bit 6 of unifiHtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiTxSGI80Activated
config_element.description_user: SGI 80MHz will be used to code packets, for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not send SGI 80MHz packets even if peer supports it. To advertise reception of SGI 80MHz packets, enable bit 5 of unifiVhtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiTxSGI160Activated
config_element.description_user: SGI 160/80+80MHz will be used to code packets, for transmit only. If disabled, chip will not send SGI 160/80+80MHz packets even if peer supports it. To advertise reception of SGI 160/80+80MHz packets, enable bit 6 of unifiVhtCapabilities.

config_element.name: unifiMacAddressRandomisation
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Enabling Mac Address Randomisation to be applied for Probe Requests when scanning.

config_element.name: unifiMacAddressRandomisationMask
config_element.description_user: FW randomises MAC Address bits that have a corresponding bit set to 0 in the MAC Mask for Probe Requests. This excludes U/L and I/G bits which will be set to Local and Individual respectively.

config_element.name: unifiMacSequenceNumberRandomisationActivated
config_element.description_user: Enabling Sequence Number Randomisation to be applied for Probe Requests when scanning. Note: Randomisation only happens, if mac address gets randomised.

config_element.name: unifiRoamingActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate Roaming functionality

config_element.name: unifiRoamingLowLatencySoftRoamingAllowed
config_element.description_user: Allow Soft Roaming functionality for some chipsets when the low latency mode is enabled.

config_element.name: unifiRoamSkipFTEmergencyRoam
config_element.description_user: Skip roaming for FT 1x and PSK security in case of emergency roaming when we received deauthenitcation/Disassociation frames from the AP.

config_element.name: unifiRoamingSoftRoamingActivatedWhenLCDIsOff
config_element.description_user: Activate Soft Roaming functionality when the LCD is off.

config_element.name: unifiRoamingSendDeauthWhenRoamingBack
config_element.description_user: Send a deauthentication frame before sending an authentication frame when roaming back.

config_element.name: unifiRoamingInP2pActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate Roaming in P2P.

config_element.name: unifiRoamRssiScanTrigger
config_element.description_user: The RSSI value, in dBm, below which roaming scan shall start.

config_element.name: unifiRoamRssiScanTriggerReset
config_element.description_user: The current channel Averaged RSSI value above which a RSSI triggered roaming scan shall stop, and the RSSI trigger shall be reset at its initial value.

config_element.name: unifiRoamRssiScanTriggerStep
config_element.description_user: The delta to apply to unifiRoamRssiScanTrigger when no eligible candidate is found.

config_element.name: unifiRoamCUScanTriggerHysteresis
config_element.description_user: Hysteresis value that subtracted from unifiRoamCUScanTrigger will result in the CU value that will stop eventual CU scans. This is an SCSC addition to ensure scans are not started/ stopped in an excessive manner.

config_element.name: unifiRoamCURssiScanTriggerHysteresis
config_element.description_user: Hysteresis value that added to unifiRoamCURssiScanTrigger will result in the RSSI value that will stop eventual CU scans. This is an SCSC addition to ensure scans are not started/ stopped in an excessive manner.

config_element.name: unifiRoamBackgroundScanPeriod
config_element.description_user: The background scan period for cached channels.

config_element.name: unifiRoamReScanPeriod
config_element.description_user: The scan period for re-scanning cached channels.

config_element.name: unifiRoamInactiveScanPeriod
config_element.description_user: The scan period for the inactive scan.

config_element.name: unifiRoamTargetRssiBeaconLost
config_element.description_user: RSSI threshold under which candidate APs are not deemed eligible for Beacon Lost scans.

config_element.name: unifiRoamTargetRssiEmergency
config_element.description_user: RSSI threshold under which candidate APs are not deemed eligible for emergency roaming scans.

config_element.name: unifiRoamConnectionQualityCheckWaitAfterConnect
config_element.description_user: The amount of time a STA will wait after connection before starting to check the MLME-installed connection quality trigger thresholds

config_element.name: unifiRoamScanBand
config_element.description_user: Indicates whether only intra-band or all-band should be used for roaming scan. 2 - Roaming across band 1 - Roaming within band

config_element.name: unifiRoamMode
config_element.description_user: Enable/Disable host resume when roaming. 0: Wake up the host all the time. 1: Only wakeup the host if the AP is not white-listed. 2: Don't wake up the host.

config_element.name: unifiRoamEAPTimeout
config_element.description_user: Timeout, in ms, for receiving the first EAP/EAPOL frame from the AP during roaming

config_element.name: unifiRoamRSSIBoost
config_element.description_user: The value in dBm of the RSSI boost for each band

config_element.name: unifiRoamCuLocal
config_element.description_user: Channel utilisation for the STA VIF, value 255=100% channel utilisation. - used for roaming

config_element.name: unifiRoamAPSelectDeltaFactor
config_element.description_user: How much higher, in percentage points, does a candidate's score needs to be in order be considered an eligible candidate? A "0" value renders all candidates eligible. Please note this applies only to soft roams.

config_element.name: unifiRoamAPSelectMinDeltaFactor
config_element.description_user: The minimum score delta with which a candidate needs to be better to be considered as an eligible candidate. This prevents ping pong roaming. Please note this applies only to soft roams.

config_element.name: unifiRoamCUWeight
config_element.description_user: Weight of CUfactor, in percentage points, in AP selection algorithm.

config_element.name: unifiRoamBtmAPSelectDeltaFactor
config_element.description_user: Delta value applied to the score of the currently connected AP to determine candidates' eligibility threshold for BTM triggered roaming scans

config_element.name: unifiRoamBtmDisregardSelectionFactor
config_element.description_user: Disregard the selection factor for BTM candidates.

config_element.name: unifiRoamBtmForceAbridged
config_element.description_user: Force abridged scan, no matter the abridged bit is set or not.

config_element.name: unifiBtmDisassociationScanDelay
config_element.description_user: Delay roaming scan to the expiration of Dissassociation Timer when disassociation is imminent.

config_element.name: unifiRoamBtmQueryTimeout
config_element.description_user: Wait time in seconds for a response to BTM Query.

config_element.name: unifiRoamCUFactor
config_element.description_user: Bi dimensional octet string table for allocating CUfactor to CU values. First index is the radio band, and the second will be CU table entry. The tables define the maximum CU value to which the values do apply(MAX CU), an OFFSET and an A value for the equation: CUfactor = OFFSET - A*(CU)/10

config_element.name: unifiRoamRssiweight
config_element.description_user: Weight of RSSI factor, in percentage points, in AP selection algorithm.

config_element.name: unifiRoamRssiFactor
config_element.description_user: Table allocating RSSIfactor to RSSI values range for each band.

config_element.name: unifiRoamRssiFactorFixedMultiplier
config_element.description_user: Table allocating fixed multiplier used to calculate the RSSIfactorScore to RSSI values range for each band.

config_element.name: unifiFtmLegacyCalibration
config_element.description_user: Table for legacy mode FTM calibration values.

config_element.name: unifiFtmHtVhtCalibration
config_element.description_user: Table for HT/VHT mode FTM calibration values.

config_element.name: unifiFtmChannelEstimate
config_element.description_user: True if hardware channel estimate based FTM is enabled. False if software IQ capture based FTM is enabled

config_element.name: unifiRoamCURssiScanTrigger
config_element.description_user: The current channel Averaged RSSI value below which a soft roaming scan shall initially start, providing high channel utilisation (see unifiRoamCUScanTrigger). This is a table indexed by frequency band.

config_element.name: unifiRoamCUScanTrigger
config_element.description_user: BSS Load / Channel Utilisation trigger above which a soft roaming scan shall initially start. This is a table indexed by frequency band.

config_element.name: unifiRoamBSSLoadMonitoringFrequency
config_element.description_user: How often, in seconds, should the BSS load be monitored? - used for roaming

config_element.name: unifiRoamBSSCUTriggerFrequency
config_element.description_user: How long, in seconds, should the BSS load be high before triggering roaming?

config_element.name: unifiRoamEapolTimeout
config_element.description_user: Maximum time, in seconds, allowed for an offloaded Eapol (4 way handshake).

config_element.name: unifiRoamBlacklistSize
config_element.description_user: Do not remove! Read by the host! And then passed up to the framework.

config_element.name: unifiRoamInactiveCount
config_element.description_user: The number of packets over which the link is considered not idle.

config_element.name: unifiRoamIdleVariationRssi
config_element.description_user: Defines the maximum RSSI variation of the current link allowed during idle roam. This parameter ensures the device is stationary.

config_element.name: unifiRoamIdleMinRssi
config_element.description_user: Defines the minimum RSSI of the current link required to perform an idle roam.

config_element.name: unifiRoamIdleInactiveTime
config_element.description_user: Defines the time interval during which the link needs to remain idle to perform an idle roam.

config_element.name: unifiRoamIdleInactiveCount
config_element.description_user: The number of packets over which the link is considered not idle.

config_element.name: unifiRoamIdleBand
config_element.description_user: Specifies when connected on which band to run the Idle Roaming algorithm. 0 for None. 1 for 2.4GHz. 2 for 5GHz. 3 for All.

config_element.name: unifiRoamIdleAPSelectDeltaFactor
config_element.description_user: Delta value applied to the score of the currently connected AP to determine candidates' eligibility threshold for Idle period triggered roaming scans.

config_element.name: unifiRoamSendInitFrameToGetNeighbors
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: The firmware can send a Neighbor request/ BTM query to get AP's neighbors. This frame upsets certification setups. Setting this MIB to false inhibits sending a Neighbor request/ BTM query to get AP's neighbors.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoScanControl
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Indicates which control path shall be evaluated in order to determine which channels should be scanned for NCHO scans.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoDfsScanMode
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Specifies how DFS channels should be scanned for roaming. For certification and Host use only.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoFullScanPeriod
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Specifies the period at which the full channel scan shall be run. For certification and Host use only.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoCachedScanPeriod
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Specifies the period at which the cached channel scan shall be run. For certification and Host use only.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoScanMaxActiveChannelTime
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Specifies the maximum time spent active scanning a channel.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoScanMaxPassiveChannelTime
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Specifies the maximum time spent passive scanning a channel.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoScanNProbe
config_element.description_user: NCHO: The number of ProbeRequest frames per channel.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoScanHomeTime
config_element.description_user: NCHO: The time, in TU, to spend NOT scanning during a HomeAway scan.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoScanHomeAwayTime
config_element.description_user: NCHO: The time, in TU, to spend scanning during a HomeAway scan.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoRssiDelta
config_element.description_user: NCHO: Specifies the RSSI delta at a potential candidate is deemed eligible.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoRssiTrigger
config_element.description_user: The current channel Averaged RSSI value below which a NCHO scan shall start.

config_element.name: unifiRoamNchoRssiTriggerHysteresis
config_element.description_user: Hysteresis value that added to unifiRoamNchoRssiTrigger will result in the RSSI value that will stop eventual NCHO scans.

config_element.name: unifiRoamFtOverDsEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enable roaming by FT over DS if BSS support it.

config_element.name: unifiRoamFtOverDsMinRssi
config_element.description_user: Defines the minimum RSSI of the roaming required to try 'FT over the DS'.

config_element.name: unifiRoamWtcActivated
config_element.description_user: If false, the FW shall ignore the Cisco VSIE(WTC) in received BTM Request frames.

config_element.name: unifiRoamTargetRssiBTM
config_element.description_user: Threshold for evaluating BTM roaming target for VIVO and MCD devices.

config_element.name: unifiAlwaysIncludeOperatingModeNotification
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Always include OMN IE in the Assoc request frames.

config_element.name: unifiOverrideEDCAParamActivated
config_element.description_user: Activate override of STA edca config parameters with unifiOverrideEDCAParam. default: True - for volcano, and False - for others

config_element.name: unifiOverrideEDCAParam
config_element.description_user: EDCA Parameters to be used if unifiOverrideEDCAParamActivated is true, indexed by unifiAccessClassIndex octet 0 - AIFSN octet 1 - [7:4] ECW MAX [3:0] ECW MIN octet 2 ~ 3 - TXOP[7:0] TXOP[15:8] in 32 usec units for both non-HT and HT connections.

config_element.name: unifiNANDefaultEDCAParam
config_element.description_user: EDCA Parameters to be used as the default in NAN, as there is no AP to specify them, indexed by unifiAccessClassIndex octet 0 - AIFSN octet 1 - [7:4] ECW MAX [3:0] ECW MIN octet 2 ~ 3 - TXOP[7:0] TXOP[15:8] in 32 usec units for both non-HT and HT connections.

config_element.name: unifiSetFixedAMPDUAggregationSize
config_element.description_user: A non 0 value defines the max number of mpdus that a ampdu can have. A 0 value tells FW to manage the aggregation size.

config_element.name: unifiRaaTxHostRate
config_element.description_user: Fixed TX rate set by Host. Ideally this should be done by the driver. 0 means "host did not specified any rate".

config_element.name: unifiWMMStallEnable
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: Enable workaround stall WMM traffic if the admitted time has been used up, used for certtification.

config_element.name: unifiLaaNssSpeculationIntervalSlotTime
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the repeatable amount of time, in ms, that firmware will start to send speculation frames for spatial streams.

config_element.name: unifiLaaNssSpeculationIntervalSlotMaxNum
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the maximum number of speculation time slot for spatial stream.

config_element.name: unifiLaaBwSpeculationIntervalSlotTime
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the repeatable amount of time, in ms, that firmware will start to send speculation frames for bandwidth.

config_element.name: unifiLaaBwSpeculationIntervalSlotMaxNum
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the maximum number of speculation time slot for bandwidth.

config_element.name: unifiLaaMcsSpeculationIntervalSlotTime
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the repeatable amount of time, in ms, that firmware will start to send speculation frames for MCS or rate index.

config_element.name: unifiLaaMcsSpeculationIntervalSlotMaxNum
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the maximum number of speculation time slot for MCS or rate index.

config_element.name: unifiLaaGiSpeculationIntervalSlotTime
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the repeatable amount of time, in ms, that firmware will start to send speculation frames for guard interval.

config_element.name: unifiLaaGiSpeculationIntervalSlotMaxNum
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the maximum number of speculation time slot for guard interval.

config_element.name: unifiLaaProtectionConfigOverride
config_element.description_user: Overrides the default Protection configuration. Only valid flags are DPIF_PEER_INFO_PROTECTION_TXOP_AMPDU and DPIF_PEER_INFO_PROTECTION_ALLOWED. Default allows protection code to work out the rules. If DPIF_PEER_INFO_PROTECTION_ALLOWED is unset, all protections are disabled. If DPIF_PEER_INFO_PROTECTION_TXOP_AMPDU is unset then, the first A-MPDU in the TxOp is no longer protected.

config_element.name: UnifiLaaTxNssAllowedMode
config_element.description_user: If non-zero,it constraites NSS mode used in LAA. Note that this MIB should be set before any connection is made. - 0 : This MIB is not used. LAA can use all possible NSS modes - 0x1 : Only 1SS mode can be used (only bit 0 is set) - 0x2 : Only 2SS mode can be used (only bit 1 is set) - 0x3 : Both 1SS and 2SS modes can be used (both bit 0 and 1 are set)

config_element.name: UnifiLaaTxDiversityBeamformEnabled
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. It is used to enable or disable TX beamformer functionality.

config_element.name: UnifiLaaTxDiversityBeamformMinMcs
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. TX Beamform is applied when MCS is same or larger than this threshold value.

config_element.name: UnifiLaaTxDiversityFixMode
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. It is used to fix TX diversity mode. With two antennas available and only one spatial stream used, then one of the following modes can be selected: - 0 : Not fixed. Tx diversity mode is automatically selected by LAA. - 1 : CDD fixed mode - 2 : Beamforming fixed mode - 3 : STBC fixed mode

config_element.name: unifiLaaSpeculationMaxTime
config_element.description_user: For Link Adaptation Algorithm. It defines the maximum time interval (in milliseconds) between speculating. So if the interval is being scaled due to not being scheduled all the time, the speculation interval will not exceed this value, even when backing off.

config_element.name: UnifiLaaAmpduInhibitTimeout
config_element.description_user: When fallback rate for an A-MPDU retransmission is non-(V)HT, we need to disable A-MPDUs to transmit the MPDU(s) at that rate. LAA does this, and re-enabled A-MPDUs based on this timeout. Note that the timeout is examined only when the current rate changes, which signifies some change in the conditions or state machine. If set to 0, A-MPDUs will restored as soon as a rate with MCS>1 or BW>20 is installed.

config_element.name: UnifiLaaRtsInhibitTimeout
config_element.description_user: When RTS protection for an A-MPDU transmission fails UnifiLaaInhibitRtsCount successive times, we disable RTS. RTS is later re-enabled based on this timeout. Note that RTS may be controlled by other means, orthogonally to this feature, e.g. Coex may have disabled it. If set to 0, RTS will be restored only after a re-association.

config_element.name: UnifiLaaInhibitRtsCount
config_element.description_user: When RTS protection for an A-MPDU transmission fails UnifiLaaInhibitRtsCount successive times, we disable RTS.

config_element.name: UnifiLaaAmpduInhibitRtsAlso
config_element.description_user: When inhibiting A-MPDU also disable RTS

config_element.name: UnifiLaaFixedMaxBandwidth
config_element.description_user: Fix maximum allowed bandwidth for transmission. - 20: allowed up to 20MHz - 40: allowed up to 40MHz - 80: allowed up to 80MHz - others: maximum bandwidth is not fixed

config_element.name: UnifiLaaMinMcsForBwChange
config_element.description_user: LAA considers to drop bandwidth when MCS drops and hits the configured value.

config_element.name: UnifiLaaLocalBwControlEnable
config_element.description_user: On the platform which supports secondary channel monitoring such as FlexiMAC, LAA can automatically adjust maximum allowed bandwidth to avoid long-delayed transmission due to busy secondary channels.

config_element.name: UnifiLaaLocalBwBusyWeigh
config_element.description_user: Weigh for busy secondary channel in LAA local BW control algorithm. 0 means this value is not applied to firmware.

config_element.name: UnifiLaaLocalBwBusyLevelThres
config_element.description_user: Busy level threshold by which LAA local BW control drops bandwidth. 0 means this value is not applied to firmware.

config_element.name: unifiFallbackShortFrameRetryDistribution
config_element.description_user: Configure the retry distribution for fallback for short frames octet 0 - Number of retries for starting rate. octet 1 - Number of retries for next rate. octet 2 - Number of retries for next rate. octet 3 - Number of retries for next rate. octet 4 - Number of retries for next rate. octet 5 - Number of retries for last rate. If 0 is written to an entry then the retries for that rate will be the short retry limit minus the sum of the retries for each rate above that entry (e.g. 15 - 5). Therefore, this should always be the value for octet 4. Also, when the starting rate has short guard enabled, the number of retries in octet 1 will be used and for the next rate in the fallback table (same MCS value, but with sgi disabled) octet 0 number of retries will be used.

config_element.name: unifiDPlaneDebug
config_element.description_user: Bit mask for turning on individual debug entities in the data_plane that if enabled effect throughput. See DPLP_DEBUG_ENTITIES_T in dplane_dplp_debug.h for bits. Default of 0x203 means dplp, ampdu and metadata logs are enabled.

config_element.name: unifiThroughputDebug
config_element.description_user: is used to access throughput related counters that can help diagnose throughput problems. The index of the MIB will access different counters, as described in SC-506328-DD. Setting any index for a VIF to any value, clears all DPLP debug stats for the MAC instance used by the VIF. This is useful mainly for debugging LAA or small scale throughput issues that require short term collection of the statistics.

config_element.name: unifiThroughputDebugReportInterval
config_element.description_user: dataplane reports throughput diag report every this interval in msec. 0 means to disable this report.

config_element.name: unifiDphpHwMonitorLogEnable
config_element.description_user: Enable/Disable DPHP HW Monitor Log

config_element.name: unifiFrameTXCounters
config_element.description_user: Frame TX Counters used by the host. These are required by MCD.

config_element.name: unifiFrameRXCounters
config_element.description_user: Frame RX Counters used by the host. These are required by MCD.

config_element.name: unifiEnableMgmtTxPacketStats
config_element.description_user: Consider management packets for TX stats counters

config_element.name: unifiReadTxPacketStatsFromStaVif
config_element.description_user: Read TX packet stats from VIF to avoid resetting of the counters during roaming - this is a Volcano requirement

config_element.name: unifiARPDetectResponseCounter
config_element.description_user: Counter used to track ARP Response frame for Enhanced ARP Detect. This is required by Volcano.

config_element.name: unifiBeaconReceived
config_element.description_user: Access point beacon received count from connected AP

config_element.name: unifiRadioLpRxRssiThresholdLower
config_element.description_user: The lower RSSI threshold for switching between low power rx and normal rx. If the RSSI avg of received frames is lower than this value for a VIF, then that VIF will vote against using low-power radio RX. Low power rx could negatively influence the receiver sensitivity.

config_element.name: unifiRadioLpRxRssiThresholdUpper
config_element.description_user: The upper RSSI threshold for switching between low power rx and normal rx. If the RSSI avg of received frames is higher than this value for a VIF, then that VIF will vote in favour of using low-power radio RX. Low power RX could negatively influence the receiver sensitivity.

config_element.name: unifiUnsyncVifLnaEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enable or disable use of the LNA for unsynchronised VIFs.

config_element.name: unifiLnaControlEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enable dynamic switching of the LNA based on RSSI for synchronised VIFs.

config_element.name: unifiLnaControlEvaluationInterval
config_element.description_user: Interval in milliseconds, for evaluating LNA control.

config_element.name: unifiLnaControlRssiThresholds
config_element.description_user: RSSI threshold table for dynamic switching of the LNA.Default values set to{-30,-40}

config_element.name: unifiModemDesenseEnabled
config_element.description_user: Enable dynamic desensing of the CCK and OFDM modems based on RSSI for STA VIFs.

config_element.name: unifiModemDesenseOption
config_element.description_user: Select which of the modems will be desensed. Only valid if unifiModemDesenseEnabled is set to true. Set the corresponding bit to enable 0: CCK desense 1: 2G4 OFDM desense 2: 5G OFDM desense 3: JD settings adjust for C1 4: Suppress during connect 5: 6G OFDM desense Also see unifiDesenseSelection

config_element.name: unifiModemDesenseOffset
config_element.description_user: The offset value for the CCK and 2G4 OFDM modem desensing. When the CCK and/or 2G4 OFDM modems are desensed, the desense value will be set to the averaged STA-AP RSSI less this parameter value. Only used when unifiModemDesenseEnabled is set to true.

config_element.name: unifiModemDesenseCap
config_element.description_user: The upper limit for dynamic desensing of the CCK and 2G4 OFDM modem. The CCK and/or 2G4 OFDM modems will not be desensed to a value in excess of this parameter. Only used when unifiModemDesenseEnabled is set to true.

config_element.name: unifiModemDesenseOffset5G
config_element.description_user: The offset value for the CCK and OFDM modem desensing. When the 5G OFDM modem is desensed, the desense value will be set to the averaged STA-AP RSSI less this parameter value. Only used when unifiModemDesenseEnabled is set to true.

config_element.name: unifiModemDesenseCap5G
config_element.description_user: The upper limit for dynamic desensing of the CCK and OFDM modem. The 5G OFDM modem will not be desensed to a value in excess of this parameter. Only used when unifiModemDesenseEnabled is set to true.

config_element.name: unifiModemDesenseOffset6G
config_element.description_user: The offset value for the CCK and OFDM modem desensing. When the 6G OFDM modem is desensed, the desense value will be set to the averaged STA-AP RSSI less this parameter value. Only used when unifiModemDesenseEnabled is set to true.

config_element.name: unifiModemDesenseCap6G
config_element.description_user: The upper limit for dynamic desensing of the CCK and OFDM modem. The 6G OFDM modem will not be desensed to a value in excess of this parameter. Only used when unifiModemDesenseEnabled is set to true.

config_element.name: unifiACRetries
config_element.description_user: It represents the number of retransmitted frames under each ac priority (indexed by unifiAccessClassIndex). This number will wrap to zero after the range is exceeded.

config_element.name: unifiACNoAcks
config_element.description_user: It represents the number of frames without ACK for each AC priority (indexed by unifiAccessClassIndex). This number will wrap to zero after the range is exceeded.

config_element.name: unifiRadioOnTime
config_element.description_user: msecs the radio is awake (32 bits number accruing over time). On multi-radio platforms an index to the radio instance is required

config_element.name: unifiRadioTxTime
config_element.description_user: msecs the radio is transmitting (32 bits number accruing over time). On multi-radio platforms an index to the radio instance is required

config_element.name: unifiRadioRxTime
config_element.description_user: msecs the radio is in active receive (32 bits number accruing over time). On multi-radio platforms an index to the radio instance is required

config_element.name: unifiRadioScanTime
config_element.description_user: msecs the radio is awake due to all scan (32 bits number accruing over time). On multi-radio platforms an index to the radio instance is required

config_element.name: unifiRadioOnTimeNan
config_element.description_user: msecs the radio is awake due to NAN operations (32 bits number accruing over time). On multi-radio platforms an index to the radio instance is required

config_element.name: unifiPSLeakyAP
config_element.description_user: AP evaluation state

config_element.name: unifiRadioMeasurementActivated
config_element.description_user: When TRUE Radio Measurements are supported.

config_element.name: unifiRadioMeasurementCapabilities
config_element.description_user: RM Enabled capabilities of the chip. See SC-503520-SP for further details.

config_element.name: unifiRMMaxMeasurementDuration
config_element.description_user: Maximum measurement duration in milliseconds for operating channel measurements, i.e. maximum channel time duration for measurement scan

config_element.name: unifiRMMaxScanCacheTime
config_element.description_user: Maximum period, in seconds, the Mlme Measurement will keep the scan result for beacon table mode. When set to zero, result never expires acting as a Golden Certification MIB for WFA VE Certification.

config_element.name: unifiRMMaxScanCacheCount
config_element.description_user: Maximum count the Mlme Measurement will maintain the scan result for beacon table mode.

config_element.name: unifiRMIgnoreIdleStaMode
config_element.description_user: When set to true, ignore idle sta mode acting as a Golden Certification MIB for WFA VE Certification.

config_element.name: unifiScanMaxCacheCount
config_element.description_user: Maximum count the Scan will maintain the scan result in cache. Zero to disable the caching.

config_element.name: unifiScanMaxCacheTime
config_element.description_user: Maximum period, in seconds, the Scan will keep the scan result in cache.

config_element.name: unifiOverrideDefaultBETXOP
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name: When set to non-zero value then this will override the BE TXOP for 11g (in 32 usec units) to the value specified here.

config_element.name: unifiOverrideDefaultBETXOPForHT
config_element.description_user: When set to non-zero value then this will override the BE TXOP for 11n and higher modulations (in 32 usec units) to the value specified here.

config_element.name: unifiRTSDurationProtectsFullTXOP
config_element.description_user: When set to true the RTS duration protects full TXOP. If false then it only covers from the RTS to the first BA, which may be followed by other bursted AMPDUs

config_element.name: unifiRXABBTrimSettings
config_element.description_user: Various settings to change RX ABB filter trim behavior.

config_element.name: unifiRadioTrimsEnable
config_element.description_user: A bitmap for enabling/disabling trims at runtime. Check unifiEnabledTrims enum for description of the possible values.

config_element.name: unifiRadioCCAThresholds
config_element.description_user: The wideband CCA ED thresholds so that the CCA-ED triggers at the regulatory value of -62 dBm.

config_element.name: unifiRadioTxIqDelay
config_element.description_user: The differential delay applied between I and Q paths in Tx.

config_element.name: unifiNarrowbandCCAThresholds
config_element.description_user: The narrowband CCA ED thresholds so that the CCA-ED triggers at the regulatory value of -62 dBm.

config_element.name: unifiHardwarePlatform
config_element.description_user: Hardware platform. This is necessary so we can apply tweaks to specific revisions, even though they might be running the same baseband and RF chip combination. Check unifiHardwarePlatform enum for description of the possible values.

config_element.name: unifiEnableFemRfLoopback
config_element.description_user: Enable RF loopback from a suitably equipped external PA.
config_element.description_internal: Bitmask of frequency bands. Set bit position to enable RF loopback. The bit position used for each band is expected to correspond to '1' left shifted by the values of the enum radio_shared_frequency_band.

config_element.name: unifiDPDTrainingDuration
config_element.description_user: Duration of DPD training (in ms).

config_element.name: unifiCurrentBssNss
config_element.description_user: Specifies current AP antenna mode: BIG DATA 0 = SISO, 1 = MIMO (2x2), 2 = MIMO (3x3), 3 = MIMO (4x4)

config_element.name: unifiCurrentBssBandwidth
config_element.description_user: Current bandwidth the STA is operating on channel_bw_20_mhz = 20, channel_bw_40_mhz = 40, channel_bw_80_mhz = 80, channel_bw_160_mhz = 160

config_element.name: unifiCurrentBssChannelFrequency
config_element.description_user: Centre frequency for the connected channel

config_element.name: unifiTestSetMaxBandwidth
config_element.description_user: Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name. Set the maximum bandwidth for a vif Setting it to 0 uses the default bandwidth as selected by firmware. channel_bw_20_mhz = 20, channel_bw_40_mhz = 40, channel_bw_80_mhz = 80, channel_bw_160_mhz = 160

config_element.name: unifiStaVifLinkNss
config_element.description_user: STA Vif (Not P2P) while connected to an AP and does not apply to TDLS links. Specifies the max number of NSS that the link can use: BIG DATA 0 = SISO, 1 = MIMO (2x2), 2 = MIMO (3x3), 3 = MIMO (4x4)

config_element.name: unifiAPMimoUsed
config_element.description_user: AP uses MU-MIMO

config_element.name: unifiHostNumAntennaControlActivated
config_element.description_user: Host has a control of number of antenna to use

config_element.name: unifiRoamingCount
config_element.description_user: Number of roams

config_element.name: unifiRoamingAKM
config_element.description_user: specifies current AKM 0 = None 1 = OKC 2 = FT (FT_1X) 3 = PSK 4 = FT_PSK 5 = PMKSA Caching

config_element.name: unifiTPCEnabled
config_element.description_user: Deprecated. Golden Certification MIB don't delete, change PSID or name

config_element.name: unifiTestTspecHack
config_element.description_user: Test only: Hack to allow in-house tspec testing

config_element.name: unifiTestTspecHackValue
config_element.description_user: Test only: Saved dialog number of tspec request action frame from the Host

config_element.name: unifiTestScanNoMedium
config_element.description_user: Test only: Stop Scan from using the Medium to allow thruput testing.

config_element.name: unifiBlockScanAfterNumSchedVif
config_element.description_user: Block Scan requests from having medium time after a specified amount of sync VIFs are schedulable. A value of 0 disables the functionality.

config_element.name: unifiNonLteUspboConfig
config_element.description_user: Deprecated. Configuration bitmap for non-LTE BlockACK control. bit0: If the bit value is 1, then preserve RX BA agreements during USPBO. If the bit value is 0, then RX BA agreements will be suppressed during USPBO bit1: If the bit value is 1, then preserve TX BA agreements during USPBO. If the bit value is 0, then TX BA agreements will be suppressed during USPBO bit2-bit15: reserved

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteDataElementInt32
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Data element read/write entry of int32 type.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteDataElementBoolean
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Data element read/write entry of boolean type.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteDataElementOctetString
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Data element read/write entry of octet string type.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteTableInt16Row
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Data element read/write entry table of int16 type.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteTableOctetStringRow
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Data element read/write entry table of octet string type.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteRemoteProcedureCallInt32
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Remote Procedure call read/write entry of int32 type.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteRemoteProcedureCallOctetString
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Remote Procedure call read/write entry of octet string type.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteInternalAPIInt16
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Data element read/write entry of int16 type via internal API.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteInternalAPIUint16
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Data element read/write entry of unsigned int16 type via internal API.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteInternalAPIUint32
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Data element read/write entry of unsigned int32 type via internal API.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteInternalAPIInt64
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Data element read/write entry of int64 type via internal API.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteInternalAPIBoolean
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Data element read/write entry of boolean type via internal API.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteInternalAPIOctetString
config_element.description_user: Reserved for HUTS tests - Data element read/write entry of octet string type via internal API.

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteInternalAPIFixSizeTableKeyIndex1
config_element.description_user: table index

config_element.name: hutsReadWriteInternalAPIFixSizeTableKeyIndex2

config_element.name: unifiRxOfdmModemDesense

config_element.description_internal: Allows ofdm modem desense values to be updated (dBm * 256). This updates the desense target level in the halmac_desense_info structure.
